58
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,560
I took Eylül away that day.

59
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:30,200
We were going to take her kidney...

60
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:37,920
Still haven't figured it out?

61
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:40,080
Mercan is a kidney patient.

62
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:42,640
She would have died if
she didn't get a transplant.

63
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:09,680
Eylül... I am so sorry
for what my father did.

64
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:13,120
For locking you up in there...

65
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:15,440
For the pain he caused you...

66
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:17,880
For your fears!

67
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:21,520
For the helplessness you
experienced at such a young age!

68
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:27,320
I am so helpless too...

69
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:35,760
I'm helpless because I'm the daughter of
a man like that, it destroys me every day!

70
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:44,440
I wish you were alive so I could fall
to my knees and truly apologize to you.

71
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:54,600
I am so mad at myself!

72
00:04:58,880 --> 00:05:00,480
I tell myself you could have seen it.

73
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:09,640
But then I say we were too
young, how was I supposed to see it.

74
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:17,160
No matter what I say...

75
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:20,480
the outcome won't change.

76
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,560
Could you leave us alone?

77
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:55,440
I couldn't look after you.

78
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:02,280
I couldn't protect you...

79
00:06:07,960 --> 00:06:09,360
I couldn't be a big brother to you.

80
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:13,800
I couldn't hold your hands
while you were struggling...

81
00:06:19,840 --> 00:06:21,600
I wish I had died instead of you.

82
00:06:30,280 --> 00:06:32,440
I feel like I'm going crazy
the more I think about it.

83
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:36,360
Who knows how scared you were?

84
00:06:40,080 --> 00:06:42,880
While they sacrificed you
without blinking an eye.

85
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,520
What were you to them anyway...

86
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:55,960
A nobody.

87
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:01,160
You died all alone, my sister...

88
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:15,320
I promise you.

89
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:19,160
I won't die without taking your revenge.

90
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:28,320
Those who caused this
pain will never know peace.

91
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,200
Son!

92
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:28,960
We are father and son.

93
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:32,560
Our bond cannot be broken.

94
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:37,720
Everyone leaves, at the end of
the day, we only have each other.

95
00:09:39,640 --> 00:09:42,760
A person's family is the
only place they can lean on...

96
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:46,240
I wish I could call you
father, that I could embrace you.

97
00:09:48,040 --> 00:09:53,440
Even if we make mistakes, break or destroy things,
we are the ones who put ourselves back together, son.

98
00:09:55,920 --> 00:09:57,040
Help me...

99
00:09:57,640 --> 00:09:59,120
Don't let them destroy your father...

100
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,000
Come let me hug you.

101
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:16,040
Open these arms for the
people you will be a father to.

102
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:21,080
Don't waste your breath.

103
00:10:48,920 --> 00:10:50,640
If I had cried, I could have convinced him.

104
00:10:51,560 --> 00:10:52,600
But I couldn't cry.

105
00:11:44,360 --> 00:11:45,360
Ateş.

106
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:48,080
Are you okay?

107
00:11:49,560 --> 00:11:52,760
Let's go to the coast and get some fresh
air if you want. It'll be good for you.

108
00:11:58,160 --> 00:11:59,800
Nothing will make me feel better.

109
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:03,680
My father killed all the hope
and happiness inside her...

110
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:07,560
Shall we walk in the garden...?

111
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:16,880
I just want to be by your side. Help-

112
00:12:16,920 --> 00:12:17,920
You can't help me.

113
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:25,320
It's better if I stay alone.

114
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:39,240
I don't understand what happened but...

115
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:44,160
Alright... Whatever you want.

116
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:04,520
What am I going to do now...

117
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:09,680
What am I going to do with you...

118
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:16,400
How am I going to get out of this
without upsetting or hurting you?

119
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:33,680
So? What are we going to do now...

120
00:13:34,680 --> 00:13:38,680
Don't be sad, my Çiçek. I'll
figure this out, don't worry.

121
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:45,816
There has to be a way
out, there definitely is.

122
00:13:45,840 --> 00:13:49,760
How are we going to find it, Malik?
Look... My God, what are we going to do?

123
00:13:50,680 --> 00:13:53,400
Are we never going to see each other again!

124
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:55,920
No, of course not. Nothing
like that will happen.

125
00:13:57,080 --> 00:13:58,080
Ah... Çiçek!

126
00:14:01,240 --> 00:14:02,240
Çiçek!

127
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:03,896
Come here, come here! Sit down right here!

128
00:14:03,920 --> 00:14:05,520
Sit! Sit down girl! Sit!

129
00:14:05,560 --> 00:14:06,560
Sit, calm down!

130
00:14:06,920 --> 00:14:08,160
Oh my God, good Lord!

131
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:12,640
Stop girl! Stop!

132
00:14:12,680 --> 00:14:15,039
Çiçek, calm down. There must be a mistake.

133
00:14:15,040 --> 00:14:17,600
A document or something must
be missing. It's nothing else.

134
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:19,240
Don't worry, I'll find a way.

135
00:14:19,560 --> 00:14:24,400
Yes, Çiçek... There must
be a way to appeal this.

136
00:14:24,560 --> 00:14:27,320
Of course there is.
We'll solve this situation.

137
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:33,280
It's not the end of the world,
girl. A solution will be found.

138
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,440
Look on the bright side.

139
00:14:37,640 --> 00:14:42,040
In a long-distance relationship,
passion and longing are always high.

140
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:44,000
You won't get bored of each other.

141
00:14:48,920 --> 00:14:50,080
What are you talking about!

142
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:52,480
Are you kidding me!

143
00:14:56,240 --> 00:14:57,520
Get out! Leave!

144
00:14:58,480 --> 00:14:59,480
Oh for God's sake!

145
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:06,520
Calm down, Çiçek.

146
00:15:06,521 --> 00:15:07,800
Okay, okay. We'll see.

147
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,200
Calm down, girl.

148
00:15:10,360 --> 00:15:11,360
-Malik? -Hmm?

149
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:16,119
Let's go ask together,
see if we can appeal it.

150
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:19,680
Of course. Okay, my Çiçek, please
don't be sad. We'll handle it.

151
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:23,120
My God.

152
00:15:23,520 --> 00:15:24,520
Don't be sad, my dear.

153
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,160
-Excuse us. -Alright son.

154
00:15:26,920 --> 00:15:28,640
No problem, girl. No problem.

155
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:31,360
If there is a problem,
there is a cure, my girl.

156
00:15:32,560 --> 00:15:33,760
What if there isn't, mom...

157
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:38,480
What if he leaves and can't
come back, mom! I can't take it!

158
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:41,320
Don't cry my dear, don't cry.

159
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:43,880
There must surely be a way.

160
00:15:44,120 --> 00:15:45,680
We will try until we find it.

161
00:15:46,040 --> 00:15:47,320
We will pray too.

162
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:48,680
God will help us.

163
00:15:49,160 --> 00:15:50,160
We'll figure it out.

164
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,360
To Eylül...

165
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:07,680
That's how that scumbag
tormented my sister.

166
00:16:54,040 --> 00:16:55,640
There's only one thing left to do, Ateş.

167
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:00,000
There is no point in
dragging this out any longer.

168
00:17:00,800 --> 00:17:03,600
This man doesn't have the right to
take one more breath in this world!

169
00:17:06,280 --> 00:17:08,200
You accuse my father of
being a murderer, right?

170
00:17:09,440 --> 00:17:10,880
Are you any different from him?

171
00:17:11,480 --> 00:17:14,920
You point a gun at
someone without blinking!

172
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:17,480
You're turning into the person you accuse!

173
00:17:20,280 --> 00:17:22,680
What are you waiting
for, come on, shoot me!

174
00:17:23,840 --> 00:17:25,600
What are you waiting for, pull the trigger!

175
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:33,040
We didn't set out on this path to kill.

176
00:17:34,840 --> 00:17:36,320
I'm not a murderer like him.

177
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:43,720
I'm not going to finish
him off that easily.

178
00:17:47,040 --> 00:17:48,680
I'll make him beg, make him crawl.

179
00:17:49,280 --> 00:17:51,720
He's going to experience
everything he lived through tenfold.

180
00:17:57,560 --> 00:17:59,000
He will beg to die.

181
00:18:06,720 --> 00:18:08,400
That's how my scales of justice work.

182
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:10,960
He must serve his punishment.

183
00:18:15,920 --> 00:18:17,120
But there is one more issue...

184
00:18:23,520 --> 00:18:25,280
Mercan doesn't know why Eylül died.

185
00:18:32,080 --> 00:18:33,600
I'll tell her when the time comes.

186
00:18:38,480 --> 00:18:39,800
If she hears it not from me...

187
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:43,720
but from someone else

188
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:53,000
I will never forgive!

189
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:56,400
Is that understood?

190
00:19:01,800 --> 00:19:06,320
One way or another, Eylül
died because of Mercan.

191
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:07,960
She was murdered...

192
00:19:10,080 --> 00:19:13,400
Instead of making them pay for this,
you're still trying to protect Mercan.

193
00:19:14,240 --> 00:19:15,240
I agree.

194
00:19:15,720 --> 00:19:16,800
Mercan is off-limits.

195
00:19:21,240 --> 00:19:22,240
She is different.

196
00:19:23,320 --> 00:19:24,320
Ms. Müzeyyen.

197
00:19:31,040 --> 00:19:32,400
Especially you, Aslı!

198
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:37,000
You heard what I said too.

199
00:20:06,120 --> 00:20:09,120
Let go of me, I'll tell you. I'll talk.

200
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:12,760
I will tell you.

201
00:20:17,360 --> 00:20:18,680
I took Eylül away that day!

202
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:21,840
Because we were going to take her kidney.

203
00:20:23,680 --> 00:20:24,680
What?

204
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:27,120
I'll kill you!

205
00:20:27,520 --> 00:20:28,760
What are you telling me?

206
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:30,240
The truth.

207
00:20:30,440 --> 00:20:31,440
No!

208
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:33,320
You're doing this so I'll kill you!

209
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:35,160
Death is a salvation for you.

210
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:36,600
Still haven't figured it out?

211
00:20:37,280 --> 00:20:38,640
Mercan was a kidney patient.

212
00:20:43,480 --> 00:20:45,360
She would have died if
there was no transplant.

213
00:20:49,520 --> 00:20:51,320
That man sacrificed my sister, Cemal.

214
00:20:56,440 --> 00:20:58,000
My little sister

215
00:21:00,320 --> 00:21:01,960
suffered pain far beyond her years.

216
00:21:08,920 --> 00:21:11,040
And in the end, without
pitying her tears...

217
00:21:14,120 --> 00:21:15,120
they killed her...

218
00:21:22,560 --> 00:21:23,840
This was her whole life...

219
00:21:31,240 --> 00:21:33,480
This is what my Eylül saw in this world.

220
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:39,720
Ateş.

221
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:46,960
May the Lord grant her the peace
she couldn't find in this world...

222
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:49,360
in the afterlife, my brother.

223
00:21:54,400 --> 00:21:55,400
It's hard...

224
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,240
May she rest in heaven.

225
00:22:14,680 --> 00:22:15,680
Amen.

226
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:20,480
Thanks Cemal. I'm glad you're by my side.

227
00:22:39,920 --> 00:22:42,880
Don't let Mercan hear this,
don't let Mercan know that.

228
00:22:43,840 --> 00:22:45,320
As if Mercan is our only problem!

229
00:22:46,480 --> 00:22:50,480
It's unclear if we came here to
get revenge or to entertain Mercan!

230
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:52,440
Aslı!

231
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:56,560
We shouldn't anger Ateş,
otherwise we'll lose him completely.

232
00:22:57,520 --> 00:22:59,280
We don't need to do anything.

233
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:03,480
It's enough for us to highlight
that Eylül died because of Mercan.

234
00:23:04,360 --> 00:23:05,960
Ateş will never be able to stomach that.

235
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:10,880
Their story is over. Over!

236
00:23:12,440 --> 00:23:14,720
Ateş has a huge weak spot for Mercan.

237
00:23:15,280 --> 00:23:18,720
Tomorrow, Mercan might even ask him
to let Haydar out of the warehouse.

238
00:23:19,880 --> 00:23:22,320
We need to be prepared
and take precautions.

239
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:25,720
I'm so bored of playing
this cat and mouse game.

240
00:23:27,640 --> 00:23:30,680
Let's strike once, strike hard, and
destroy everything, that's what I want.

241
00:23:32,800 --> 00:23:35,440
Listen to me. Listen to me.

242
00:23:38,040 --> 00:23:39,840
Alright... Okay mom, we'll do as you say.

243
00:23:45,680 --> 00:23:47,480
You won't stop, I know.

244
00:23:48,400 --> 00:23:49,880
You're going to ruin everything.

245
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:51,920
Oh Aslı, oh...

246
00:23:52,600 --> 00:23:54,520
This love has blinded you too.

247
00:24:12,600 --> 00:24:13,840
Something happened, but what?

248
00:24:15,240 --> 00:24:16,240
He is upset.

249
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:19,880
It's like he's avoiding looking at me...

250
00:24:20,640 --> 00:24:22,120
He doesn't want to talk.

251
00:24:23,720 --> 00:24:24,840
He looks grim.

252
00:24:25,200 --> 00:24:28,360
The man who's been trying to
make it up to me for days is gone...

253
00:24:28,840 --> 00:24:30,640
and it's like someone else took his place.

254
00:24:31,200 --> 00:24:33,240
But he is the one who deceived you.

255
00:24:33,840 --> 00:24:35,320
He is the one who hid his identity.

256
00:24:35,720 --> 00:24:37,520
What happened now that
he's acting this way?

257
00:24:38,640 --> 00:24:42,880
Because of my father, very
difficult things happened in the past.

258
00:24:44,280 --> 00:24:46,280
It's normal for him to have mood swings.

259
00:24:46,840 --> 00:24:50,240
But he knew these from
the start. It's not new.

260
00:24:51,160 --> 00:24:52,680
That's what I'm afraid of, Demet.

261
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:56,840
It's like there's
something else I don't know.

262
00:24:57,920 --> 00:25:00,720
There's a growing unease inside me.

263
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:03,600
I feel like bad things are going to happen.

264
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:15,000
We'll talk later, good night.

265
00:25:33,280 --> 00:25:34,280
How are you?

266
00:25:37,120 --> 00:25:38,680
I need some silence.

267
00:25:52,920 --> 00:25:53,920
Sorry.

268
00:25:55,480 --> 00:25:56,560
I didn't mean to hurt you.

269
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:03,040
It's just that there are
things I can't figure out.

270
00:26:06,280 --> 00:26:07,800
Is there something else I don't know?

271
00:26:26,560 --> 00:26:28,000
Mercan was a kidney patient!

272
00:26:28,840 --> 00:26:30,880
She would have died if
she didn't get a transplant.

273
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:33,240
The only matching kidney was Eylül's.

274
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:35,040
We took her kidney.

275
00:26:43,040 --> 00:26:45,520
If there's anything I
can do, just say the word.

276
00:26:49,840 --> 00:26:51,120
I'm going to get some fresh air.

277
00:26:52,040 --> 00:26:53,040
You go to sleep.

278
00:26:54,240 --> 00:26:55,240
Let me come too...

279
00:26:56,680 --> 00:26:59,440
You stay here. It's cold outside.

280
00:28:34,160 --> 00:28:36,240
What are you hiding from me, Ateş?

281
00:28:59,240 --> 00:29:00,240
Malik? Çiçek.

282
00:29:00,920 --> 00:29:02,120
What happened?

283
00:29:03,120 --> 00:29:05,096
Is there a solution? There is,
right, you're not leaving, right?

284
00:29:05,120 --> 00:29:07,320
Wait, calm down my
dear. Come sit down here.

285
00:29:07,800 --> 00:29:08,880
Sit down so I can tell you.

286
00:29:11,360 --> 00:29:12,560
Hmm? Tell me.

287
00:29:14,480 --> 00:29:15,840
Calm down, my love.

288
00:29:16,160 --> 00:29:18,520
They're not going to grab us
by the arm and throw us out...

289
00:29:20,320 --> 00:29:23,920
I called a few places but
couldn't learn anything solid.

290
00:29:24,920 --> 00:29:27,040
I need to go to the Immigration Office.

291
00:29:27,680 --> 00:29:30,200
We'll find out what's what from there.

292
00:29:31,840 --> 00:29:34,000
Where did this come from
all of a sudden, Malik?

293
00:29:35,360 --> 00:29:37,320
Isn't it so ridiculous...

294
00:29:37,600 --> 00:29:40,760
Just when we reunited! It's
like someone is trying to stop us.

295
00:29:47,080 --> 00:29:49,800
No one can stop us. No one can separate us.

296
00:29:50,600 --> 00:29:53,960
As long as we never let go
of our hands. Let's stand tall.

297
00:29:54,840 --> 00:29:57,400
We can endure anything. Anything.

298
00:30:00,680 --> 00:30:01,760
My God...

299
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:07,440
Look, we're not letting
go of each other's hands.

300
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:12,920
Please don't let go of our
hands either. Show us the way...

301
00:30:18,360 --> 00:30:19,360
Come.

302
00:30:27,920 --> 00:30:31,320
(speaking Arabic)

303
00:30:38,600 --> 00:30:39,600
Amen.

304
00:30:40,480 --> 00:30:41,480
It will all pass.

305
00:31:04,480 --> 00:31:05,480
My Eylül...

306
00:31:07,440 --> 00:31:08,440
My sister...

307
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:11,560
How could they be so cruel to you...

308
00:33:01,520 --> 00:33:02,520
Ateş.

309
00:33:09,720 --> 00:33:10,720
Did I wake you?

310
00:33:11,160 --> 00:33:12,160
Mm-mmm.

311
00:33:14,480 --> 00:33:15,680
I'm still sleeping.

312
00:33:18,960 --> 00:33:20,320
You're talking in your sleep then.

313
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:23,960
Yes. You are in my dream right now.

314
00:33:25,520 --> 00:33:26,720
I hope it's a good dream.

315
00:33:29,480 --> 00:33:30,480
Very beautiful.

316
00:33:34,240 --> 00:33:35,320
Very beautiful.

317
00:33:40,480 --> 00:33:42,240
You are holding my hand warmly.

318
00:33:46,800 --> 00:33:49,120
I am telling you that I
am always by your side.

319
00:33:55,440 --> 00:33:57,160
I say I will never let go of your hand...

320
00:33:59,400 --> 00:34:02,880
And then you tell me that you love me.

321
00:34:04,800 --> 00:34:05,800
Is that so.

322
00:34:08,160 --> 00:34:11,120
You tell me that you love me.

323
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:14,520
I love you.

324
00:34:17,560 --> 00:34:18,560
I love you too.

325
00:34:22,880 --> 00:34:23,880
Good night.

326
00:34:24,960 --> 00:34:25,960
Good night.

327
