337
00:36:29,600 --> 00:36:31,280
I knew you had pain inside you.

338
00:36:34,840 --> 00:36:37,000
But I couldn't have
imagined such a great pain.

339
00:36:42,160 --> 00:36:47,280
You lived the pain I don't
even dare to think about...

340
00:36:59,280 --> 00:37:00,280
No...

341
00:37:08,360 --> 00:37:09,360
No...

342
00:37:10,120 --> 00:37:11,120
Don't... Ateş?

343
00:37:12,840 --> 00:37:13,840
Let her go...

344
00:37:14,160 --> 00:37:15,160
Ateş, wake up.

345
00:37:16,120 --> 00:37:17,120
Eylül!

346
00:37:17,880 --> 00:37:18,520
Ateş!

347
00:37:18,800 --> 00:37:19,800
Sister!

348
00:37:21,040 --> 00:37:22,040
Ateş?

349
00:37:23,680 --> 00:37:24,680
Eylül!

350
00:37:25,880 --> 00:37:26,880
Ateş!

351
00:37:27,600 --> 00:37:29,800
You had a nightmare. It's all over.

352
00:37:30,320 --> 00:37:31,760
Look, I am here.

353
00:37:47,800 --> 00:37:48,800
It's over.

354
00:37:55,160 --> 00:37:56,160
You're okay, right?

355
00:37:56,680 --> 00:37:58,080
Okay, it's passed. I'm fine.

356
00:38:29,280 --> 00:38:30,280
Ateş...

357
00:38:48,960 --> 00:38:52,200
Thirty, seventy, forty... There
are three reference lines here.

358
00:38:52,640 --> 00:38:53,640
Good morning.

359
00:38:55,680 --> 00:38:58,000
I hope you haven't had breakfast.

360
00:38:58,040 --> 00:39:01,720
I brought you some of the
famous pastry from my hometown.

361
00:39:02,400 --> 00:39:03,400
Smells wonderful!

362
00:39:03,440 --> 00:39:04,440
No!

363
00:39:04,880 --> 00:39:08,200
Yaşar Abi... I'll be the
host. I'm waiting for my desk.

364
00:39:09,520 --> 00:39:11,200
He's going to be the host.

365
00:39:11,360 --> 00:39:13,560
He's grown enough to host his elders now.

366
00:39:14,680 --> 00:39:17,800
I can't resist pastry. I don't
care about calories right now.

367
00:39:18,080 --> 00:39:19,320
Here you go, Ms. Zahide.

368
00:39:19,640 --> 00:39:22,360
I can't resist it either.
Especially not the famous one...

369
00:39:29,400 --> 00:39:30,400
Give it here, come on.

370
00:39:34,640 --> 00:39:36,920
This is for Demet. Maybe
she hasn't had breakfast.

371
00:39:40,720 --> 00:39:43,720
It's so nice that you
stayed friends like this.

372
00:39:47,440 --> 00:39:49,400
Don't talk with your mouth full!

373
00:39:52,560 --> 00:39:53,560
Oh sorry, right!

374
00:39:53,720 --> 00:39:55,560
So be quiet, your mouth is still full!

375
00:39:57,760 --> 00:39:58,880
Okay don't get mad, sorry...

376
00:40:00,040 --> 00:40:01,120
I swallowed. Don't get mad.

377
00:40:06,560 --> 00:40:07,560
So?

378
00:40:08,280 --> 00:40:09,280
Burak.

379
00:40:09,320 --> 00:40:13,920
Are Ateş and Mercan okay? They haven't
been coming to the company lately.

380
00:40:15,720 --> 00:40:18,320
They are fine... As far as
I know, there is no problem.

381
00:40:20,360 --> 00:40:22,560
-As far as you know... -Hm-hmm.

382
00:40:24,200 --> 00:40:28,200
I'm going to get tea. You can't
eat it dry. Do you want some?

383
00:40:28,720 --> 00:40:29,360
I'll have some.

384
00:40:29,600 --> 00:40:30,600
What about you?

385
00:40:30,640 --> 00:40:31,680
-Black? -Black.

386
00:40:31,760 --> 00:40:33,360
-Black? Perfect. -Black.

387
00:40:33,400 --> 00:40:34,400
I'll bring it right away.

388
00:40:36,920 --> 00:40:40,640
There is definitely a problem, I can tell.

389
00:40:40,920 --> 00:40:42,920
Did you see how quickly
he closed the subject?

390
00:40:43,400 --> 00:40:44,400
He went running.

391
00:40:44,920 --> 00:40:47,680
If you're going to gossip, shut up. Okay?

392
00:40:49,720 --> 00:40:51,160
What did I do, Zahide?

393
00:40:51,760 --> 00:40:53,520
Enjoy your meal, Yaşar...

394
00:40:56,960 --> 00:40:58,760
Let's see what else is here.

395
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:00,600
Mmmh.

396
00:41:01,200 --> 00:41:02,200
There is also poğaça.

397
00:41:04,640 --> 00:41:06,240
Anyway, let him come and we'll continue.

398
00:41:11,480 --> 00:41:12,880
What kind of fate is this, Cemal!

399
00:41:16,960 --> 00:41:19,360
I don't know how to act or what to feel!

400
00:41:21,600 --> 00:41:23,080
What am I going to tell Mercan now...

401
00:41:30,160 --> 00:41:31,480
I know she is not to blame...

402
00:41:32,080 --> 00:41:33,680
I break her heart unintentionally.

403
00:41:36,360 --> 00:41:37,680
Then I feel sad about that too.

404
00:41:43,480 --> 00:41:45,000
She feels that I'm hiding things.

405
00:41:46,040 --> 00:41:50,080
I know if I tell her everything,
she'll be completely devastated.

406
00:41:55,800 --> 00:41:57,480
I'm stuck between a rock and a hard place.

407
00:41:59,240 --> 00:42:00,520
I really am in limbo.

408
00:42:03,680 --> 00:42:04,680
Ateş.

409
00:42:05,720 --> 00:42:08,920
Have you ever come
across beautiful things...

410
00:42:09,440 --> 00:42:10,680
without making sacrifices...

411
00:42:11,360 --> 00:42:13,600
without fighting for them,
facing no difficulties?

412
00:42:14,680 --> 00:42:15,800
I haven't, for example.

413
00:42:17,080 --> 00:42:19,240
I've stumbled upon a few
coincidences, of course.

414
00:42:19,560 --> 00:42:21,520
But their lifespan was short.

415
00:42:27,600 --> 00:42:29,280
Your fire is big enough to burn you both.

416
00:42:30,720 --> 00:42:32,480
You will make sacrifices if necessary.

417
00:42:33,560 --> 00:42:36,040
You will fight to the end if necessary.

418
00:42:42,400 --> 00:42:44,720
I think you should
first trust your heart...

419
00:42:45,400 --> 00:42:46,840
and then Mercan. Be patient.

420
00:42:49,040 --> 00:42:50,600
Time is a strange thing.

421
00:42:50,640 --> 00:42:52,280
Sometimes it cures all troubles.

422
00:42:53,440 --> 00:42:55,520
I think that's what both of you need.

423
00:42:57,680 --> 00:42:59,961
There is something I need to
do without wasting any time.

424
00:43:03,320 --> 00:43:04,960
The doctor who performed Eylül's surgery,

425
00:43:05,800 --> 00:43:08,360
the one who is an accomplice to
her death... I have to find him.

426
00:43:12,640 --> 00:43:14,840
Maybe they sacrificed
other children like this too.

427
00:43:19,960 --> 00:43:21,320
Not just for Eylül.

428
00:43:22,920 --> 00:43:24,600
I want justice for all of them.

429
00:43:26,160 --> 00:43:27,520
Well said.

430
00:43:28,320 --> 00:43:29,720
Let me start investigating.

431
00:43:30,080 --> 00:43:32,240
Yes. Do whatever it takes.

432
00:43:33,760 --> 00:43:35,480
And I'll try to make Haydar talk.

433
00:43:39,120 --> 00:43:40,520
And when I find the doctor...

434
00:43:43,160 --> 00:43:45,480
I will do what needs to
be done with my own hands.

435
00:44:09,560 --> 00:44:10,680
It just doesn't fit!

436
00:44:11,520 --> 00:44:14,080
Of course it won't fit, it's a tiny room.

437
00:44:15,560 --> 00:44:17,000
It's not even a room, it's a closet.

438
00:44:18,280 --> 00:44:20,120
Do I really deserve this rat hole!

439
00:44:30,160 --> 00:44:32,480
So, what did you do, bride?

440
00:44:33,240 --> 00:44:34,880
Were you able to settle into your room?

441
00:44:35,600 --> 00:44:36,600
You see this, right?

442
00:44:37,560 --> 00:44:38,920
I can't fit any of my things here.

443
00:44:39,520 --> 00:44:41,280
Is this what a new
bride's room looks like!?

444
00:44:47,440 --> 00:44:49,680
We are up to our necks in trouble.

445
00:44:50,040 --> 00:44:53,400
We are in no position to deal
with your ridiculous problems!

446
00:44:54,200 --> 00:44:56,720
Since we are family,
you have to deal with it.

447
00:44:57,840 --> 00:45:01,200
What a family! Just great!

448
00:45:04,640 --> 00:45:08,080
Of course, since you have to
be separated from your beloved...

449
00:45:08,480 --> 00:45:11,560
you're jealous, I understand you.

450
00:45:20,000 --> 00:45:21,480
But everyone has their own problems.

451
00:45:22,080 --> 00:45:25,520
I reunited with my love,
and now I want to settle in.

452
00:45:25,880 --> 00:45:27,080
Try to understand me too.

453
00:45:27,480 --> 00:45:28,480
Don't drag it out, Zehra!

454
00:45:28,920 --> 00:45:32,480
Since you say we're family,
our problem is your problem too.

455
00:45:32,920 --> 00:45:34,400
We don't have mine and yours.

456
00:45:37,520 --> 00:45:40,720
There's no mine and yours, but
this is a problem too, mother Binnaz.

457
00:45:46,280 --> 00:45:49,200
May God help you too,
sister-in-law. Separation is hard.

458
00:45:51,280 --> 00:45:54,040
Anyway, let me go get my other
suitcase. If I can fit it, of course.

459
00:46:03,920 --> 00:46:04,920
Mom...

460
00:46:08,040 --> 00:46:10,000
Is Malik really going to go...

461
00:46:15,040 --> 00:46:16,520
I can't live without Malik.

462
00:46:20,240 --> 00:46:22,680
Oh my beautiful girl. Oh my dear.

463
00:46:23,320 --> 00:46:26,400
Has a lighthouse ever been seen going out?

464
00:46:27,360 --> 00:46:28,360
That light always burns.

465
00:46:28,400 --> 00:46:31,360
It burns so sailors can find their way.

466
00:46:32,600 --> 00:46:35,080
Your love is also a love that great.

467
00:46:35,240 --> 00:46:38,520
The greater the love,
the more tests it faces.

468
00:46:39,320 --> 00:46:45,080
If your love is real,
be a light to each other.

469
00:46:49,600 --> 00:46:52,120
That's the only way you'll
get out of this darkness.

470
00:46:58,520 --> 00:47:01,920
Come on, get up. We have
a ton of work to handle.

471
00:47:02,520 --> 00:47:06,640
My beautiful girl. We
will overcome these too.

472
00:47:46,400 --> 00:47:47,800
You know I'm stressed these days.

473
00:47:48,560 --> 00:47:50,480
If I unintentionally hurt you, I'm sorry.

474
00:47:54,600 --> 00:47:56,120
There are no faults in you.

475
00:48:06,360 --> 00:48:08,280
Let me just look at you with love.

476
00:48:14,640 --> 00:48:15,640
Wouldn't you get bored?

477
00:48:56,400 --> 00:48:57,400
That was beautiful.

478
00:49:01,360 --> 00:49:05,400
Think about yourself these days, not me.

479
00:49:07,440 --> 00:49:08,840
Because I always think about you...

480
00:49:13,480 --> 00:49:15,640
Both you and I are going
through very difficult days.

481
00:49:16,880 --> 00:49:19,480
It's normal for us to falter, to get angry.

482
00:49:23,280 --> 00:49:26,800
We have to show
understanding to each other.

483
00:49:29,040 --> 00:49:31,600
Otherwise we can't get past these days.

484
00:49:35,040 --> 00:49:36,040
For example...

485
00:49:39,080 --> 00:49:41,520
When I do this to you, you
have to be understanding.

486
00:49:42,880 --> 00:49:44,240
You want a war.

487
00:49:45,040 --> 00:49:46,840
Love is a war sometimes, don't you know?

488
00:49:47,960 --> 00:49:49,560
Then I'll fight too.

489
00:49:50,520 --> 00:49:52,080
(Laughter)

490
00:49:52,800 --> 00:49:53,800
Come here.

491
00:49:56,640 --> 00:50:00,120
(Laughter)

492
00:50:08,640 --> 00:50:10,360
Stop, okay!

493
00:50:11,200 --> 00:50:12,200
Okay!

494
00:50:12,280 --> 00:50:14,160
-Do you surrender? -I do. Okay.

495
00:50:15,400 --> 00:50:16,400
Let's make peace.

496
00:50:17,120 --> 00:50:18,120
Let's make peace then.

497
00:50:28,640 --> 00:50:29,640
You remembered.

498
00:50:31,000 --> 00:50:35,120
One of the rare beautiful
things I remember.

499
00:50:37,360 --> 00:50:38,720
You were like this as a child too.

500
00:50:40,360 --> 00:50:42,760
You wouldn't hurt anyone,
didn't want to stay mad at anyone.

501
00:50:45,680 --> 00:50:48,120
And you knew well how
to win my heart back...

502
00:50:49,200 --> 00:50:50,200
Do you remember...

503
00:50:50,880 --> 00:50:52,840
One day you took my
notebook and scribbled in it.

504
00:50:53,520 --> 00:50:56,400
You drew a house with smoke
supposedly coming out of the chimney.

505
00:50:58,320 --> 00:50:59,320
I remember.

506
00:51:00,640 --> 00:51:02,320
And you got mad and scolded me.

507
00:51:03,680 --> 00:51:07,280
Then you brought me a
beautiful sketchbook and colors.

508
00:51:08,520 --> 00:51:09,520
And inside...

509
00:51:14,960 --> 00:51:16,040
A flower like this.

510
00:51:23,080 --> 00:51:27,360
Then Eylül came and scribbled in
both our notebooks and ran away.

511
00:51:31,920 --> 00:51:32,920
This flower...

512
00:51:33,720 --> 00:51:35,280
Maybe it's not in the soil anymore...

513
00:51:41,280 --> 00:51:47,720
It won't blow in the wind or get wet in the
rain, but it will have a new life with me.

514
00:51:53,360 --> 00:51:55,400
I will keep it for the rest of my life.

515
00:52:13,080 --> 00:52:16,600
What a mess they made of this place!

516
00:52:17,640 --> 00:52:19,480
These are quite dirty.

517
00:52:20,800 --> 00:52:21,960
Let me put this here for now.

518
00:52:22,880 --> 00:52:23,880
-Mom. -Hmm?

519
00:52:24,640 --> 00:52:28,680
We will go to the Immigration
Office with Malik, don't worry.

520
00:52:28,760 --> 00:52:30,080
Go and find out.

521
00:52:30,120 --> 00:52:32,920
I hope it's some kind of mistake
so they don't send the poor boy away.

522
00:52:33,560 --> 00:52:35,360
I hope so, mother.

523
00:52:35,640 --> 00:52:36,640
God be with you.

524
00:52:37,800 --> 00:52:39,720
I can't fit into that tiny room.

525
00:52:40,280 --> 00:52:43,840
While you should be busy with your wife's
problems, you're worrying about others!

526
00:52:50,280 --> 00:52:52,680
We'll handle it, honey.

527
00:52:52,880 --> 00:52:54,440
Let's just save this kid first.

528
00:52:54,840 --> 00:52:57,200
Sure, I'll just keep waiting...

529
00:52:57,840 --> 00:53:00,280
Girl, you're obsessed with this room stuff.

530
00:53:00,640 --> 00:53:02,616
What is this anyway. It's
not like you're on the streets!

531
00:53:02,640 --> 00:53:04,200
This boy's situation is more serious.

532
00:53:04,360 --> 00:53:05,600
Show some understanding!

533
00:53:08,680 --> 00:53:12,680
You go son, go, I'll
take care of the bride.

534
00:53:12,760 --> 00:53:14,120
I'll win her heart right now.

535
00:53:16,600 --> 00:53:17,680
Okay, okay mom.

536
00:53:18,880 --> 00:53:19,880
See you.

537
00:53:33,240 --> 00:53:35,320
Zehra, you've started talking too much.

538
00:53:35,720 --> 00:53:37,280
Let your hands work, not your mouth.

539
00:53:37,760 --> 00:53:39,639
You must be bored from standing around.

540
00:53:39,640 --> 00:53:42,080
Take these pillowcases.

541
00:53:42,120 --> 00:53:45,120
Take them and put them in the
washing machine at the mansion.

542
00:53:46,400 --> 00:53:48,040
Come on, don't just stand there, come on!

543
00:53:48,240 --> 00:53:50,896
Idle hands do the devil's work, let
your hands work and lighten your heart.

544
00:53:50,920 --> 00:53:52,560
Come on, take these.

545
00:53:59,200 --> 00:54:00,200
Like this?

546
00:54:00,480 --> 00:54:01,720
Good job, just like that.

547
00:54:02,400 --> 00:54:03,840
As if it's your first time doing it.

548
00:54:46,680 --> 00:54:48,440
I brought you some wet wipes.

549
00:55:12,560 --> 00:55:13,560
I wonder...

550
00:55:15,600 --> 00:55:17,440
If these painful things hadn't happened...

551
00:55:19,880 --> 00:55:21,520
Would our paths have crossed again?

552
00:55:29,040 --> 00:55:30,880
Would we have met and
loved each other again?

553
00:55:45,720 --> 00:55:49,040
If fate wills it, it can bring two people
together from opposite ends of the world.

554
00:55:52,080 --> 00:55:55,640
Or it can make them strangers
even in the same house.

555
00:56:02,720 --> 00:56:03,760
We experienced both.

556
00:56:08,360 --> 00:56:09,360
Yes.

557
00:56:10,240 --> 00:56:13,120
We went through more than
a single heart can bear.

558
00:56:24,560 --> 00:56:26,960
You are the closest person to
me in this world, I know that.

559
00:56:31,080 --> 00:56:33,040
But I also see the abyss between us.

560
00:56:38,400 --> 00:56:39,520
An abyss full of lies,

561
00:56:40,720 --> 00:56:41,720
pain,

562
00:56:42,800 --> 00:56:44,400
and tears.

563
00:56:47,520 --> 00:56:49,200
Will we be able to overcome it, Ateş?

564
00:56:53,720 --> 00:56:55,720
It's not always good
to talk about everything.

565
00:57:00,000 --> 00:57:01,560
Sometimes you need time

566
00:57:03,680 --> 00:57:04,680
for the right answers.

567
00:57:07,360 --> 00:57:09,160
Love conquers all.

568
00:57:10,840 --> 00:57:12,400
It endures all answers.

569
00:57:13,960 --> 00:57:15,880
It turns all impossibilities
into possibilities.

570
00:57:26,680 --> 00:57:28,080
It crosses all abysses...

571
00:57:39,000 --> 00:57:41,240
I'll be waiting for you
at the edge of that abyss...

572
00:57:42,080 --> 00:57:44,160
I'll wait despite the lies and the pain.

573
00:57:48,160 --> 00:57:51,480
That abyss is much deeper
than you think. Much darker...

574
00:57:57,720 --> 00:57:58,720
Are you cold?

575
00:57:59,800 --> 00:58:00,800
Yes.

576
00:58:01,760 --> 00:58:03,440
Shall we go inside and drink some hot tea?

577
00:58:04,080 --> 00:58:05,560
You go, I'm coming.

578
00:58:21,440 --> 00:58:22,440
(sighs)

579
00:58:47,480 --> 00:58:48,480
Mercan.

580
00:58:50,240 --> 00:58:53,640
They locked your father in
the basement like an animal.

581
00:58:55,800 --> 00:58:57,960
I have no one left but you.

582
00:58:58,680 --> 00:59:00,080
Don't you turn your back on me too.

583
00:59:01,960 --> 00:59:04,160
We have no one but each other, my girl.

584
00:59:06,200 --> 00:59:07,880
And my father locked them in there?

585
00:59:09,360 --> 00:59:11,000
We don't have a family anymore, mom.

586
00:59:12,160 --> 00:59:14,160
My father destroyed our
family with what he did.

587
00:59:14,920 --> 00:59:17,000
He is human, he can make mistakes!

588
00:59:18,280 --> 00:59:19,280
Mistakes?

589
00:59:19,920 --> 00:59:23,120
Tormenting little children
cannot be called a mistake!

590
00:59:24,120 --> 00:59:25,680
They were defenseless.

591
00:59:26,360 --> 00:59:28,480
They had no one to protect them!

592
00:59:31,680 --> 00:59:33,920
Do you know who harms children?

593
00:59:34,680 --> 00:59:36,560
Who hurts them without feeling pain...

594
00:59:38,160 --> 00:59:39,160
Pure evil!

595
00:59:40,440 --> 00:59:43,200
Only the most evil people
in this world harm children!

596
00:59:44,480 --> 00:59:45,880
My father is one of them!

597
00:59:46,480 --> 00:59:47,680
And you are too!

598
00:59:48,680 --> 00:59:50,440
You knew everything
from the very beginning.

599
00:59:51,720 --> 00:59:53,520
You just kept living without caring!

600
00:59:56,320 --> 00:59:57,720
You don't have a heart either!

601
01:00:31,520 --> 01:00:33,160
Who performed Eylül's surgery?

602
01:00:35,000 --> 01:00:36,000
I don't remember.

603
01:00:38,280 --> 01:00:39,280
You will remember.

604
01:00:40,480 --> 01:00:42,000
You will give me that doctor's name!

605
01:00:42,080 --> 01:00:43,200
So many years have passed...

606
01:00:43,720 --> 01:00:46,080
Haydar! Do not test my patience!

607
01:00:46,320 --> 01:00:47,840
What will change if you know his name?

608
01:00:48,040 --> 01:00:49,880
A lot! Talk!

609
01:00:51,960 --> 01:00:53,560
I'm asking for the last time.

610
01:00:55,360 --> 01:00:56,360
Feridun...

611
01:00:59,440 --> 01:01:01,320
Feridun! I don't remember his last name.

612
01:01:07,400 --> 01:01:09,400
I did everything because
I loved my daughter!

613
01:01:16,440 --> 01:01:18,040
I sacrificed a life for my daughter.

614
01:01:18,520 --> 01:01:20,200
I chose Mercan, I chose Mercan!

615
01:01:38,480 --> 01:01:40,000
I wonder what they did?

616
01:01:41,320 --> 01:01:43,200
It's been hours and there is no news.

617
01:01:44,480 --> 01:01:48,960
They are trying to find
out what's what, my girl.

618
01:01:49,000 --> 01:01:50,680
They will call, don't worry.

619
01:01:52,080 --> 01:01:53,080
Ah!

620
01:01:54,400 --> 01:01:55,400
Hello.

621
01:01:58,440 --> 01:02:00,880
No. Wrong number.

622
01:02:06,680 --> 01:02:09,120
I got scared thinking it was bad news.

623
01:02:10,040 --> 01:02:13,040
Don't fall into despair
just because a paper arrived.

624
01:02:13,720 --> 01:02:17,280
You will overcome so many
more obstacles in married life.

625
01:02:18,160 --> 01:02:21,160
Love brings a lot of joy,
but its burden is heavy too.

626
01:02:23,840 --> 01:02:26,880
You'll say 'I will do it'.
You'll say 'I will overcome it'.

627
01:02:27,120 --> 01:02:30,480
As you say this, the Lord will
breathe strength into your heart.

628
01:02:34,720 --> 01:02:35,720
-Mom. -Huh?

629
01:02:36,640 --> 01:02:38,640
Now that something like
this has happened to us...

630
01:02:41,520 --> 01:02:43,040
I made a decision, mom.

631
01:02:46,520 --> 01:02:47,520
If...

632
01:02:49,920 --> 01:02:52,520
If Malik leaves and won't come back

633
01:02:54,840 --> 01:02:56,400
I will go with him too.

634
01:02:59,400 --> 01:03:01,280
You are my everything.

635
01:03:02,520 --> 01:03:04,920
You, my brother, you are my life.

636
01:03:05,320 --> 01:03:07,560
But I don't want to be
separated from Malik either, mom.

637
01:03:10,200 --> 01:03:11,800
Mom, aren't you going to say anything?

638
01:03:14,840 --> 01:03:16,360
Mom? You understand me, right?

639
01:03:38,720 --> 01:03:42,280
You fill your waters and
I'll make you a nice sandwich.

640
01:03:42,840 --> 01:03:44,520
You haven't eaten anything since morning.

641
01:04:07,520 --> 01:04:09,520
I did everything because
I loved my daughter!

642
01:04:10,520 --> 01:04:12,080
I sacrificed a life for my daughter.

643
01:04:12,600 --> 01:04:14,280
I chose Mercan, I chose Mercan!

644
01:04:25,080 --> 01:04:29,520
Ah! Ateş! What are you doing! Stop! Stop!

645
01:04:31,000 --> 01:04:33,920
Are you okay? Give me your hand,
let's put it under water. Come.

646
01:04:34,440 --> 01:04:35,440
I'm fine.

647
01:04:40,080 --> 01:04:41,080
Does it hurt?

648
01:04:45,960 --> 01:04:46,960
Wait...

649
01:04:55,960 --> 01:04:56,960
Give me your hand.

650
01:04:58,560 --> 01:04:59,560
You're okay, right?

651
01:05:00,440 --> 01:05:01,440
I'm fine.

652
01:05:04,120 --> 01:05:05,120
You are not fine.

653
01:05:06,440 --> 01:05:07,440
There is something wrong.

654
01:05:08,440 --> 01:05:09,880
Why won't you tell me?

655
01:05:11,400 --> 01:05:12,400
I'm fine.

656
01:05:14,920 --> 01:05:15,920
Let it burn.

657
01:05:21,880 --> 01:05:23,520
Nothing can cool my inside.

658
01:05:51,280 --> 01:05:54,040
There is this. I wrote that down too.

659
01:05:57,560 --> 01:05:58,560
(indistinct dialogue)

660
01:05:59,280 --> 01:06:00,280
Write this part too.

661
01:06:01,120 --> 01:06:02,120
Exactly like that.

662
01:06:02,920 --> 01:06:04,040
(indistinct dialogue)

663
01:06:06,520 --> 01:06:07,520
Demet.

664
01:06:18,720 --> 01:06:19,920
Is there any news from Mercan?

665
01:06:22,040 --> 01:06:23,240
She's constantly on my mind...

666
01:06:24,880 --> 01:06:26,840
She's not safe in that
house, among those people.

667
01:06:27,520 --> 01:06:31,360
You're right... But
Mercan still trusts Ateş.

668
01:06:39,000 --> 01:06:40,000
Out of desperation.

669
01:06:41,240 --> 01:06:42,720
She acts this way out of fear.

670
01:06:46,440 --> 01:06:48,721
I will suggest she moves into
the house I bought for her.

671
01:06:49,720 --> 01:06:51,640
The one you bought for her?

672
01:06:52,320 --> 01:06:53,320
Yes.

673
01:06:54,280 --> 01:06:56,080
Brother, look...

674
01:06:56,920 --> 01:06:58,800
Mercan wouldn't accept something like that.

675
01:06:59,640 --> 01:07:00,640
Don't push it.

676
01:07:02,000 --> 01:07:04,440
For your own good,
give up on this love now.

677
01:07:06,320 --> 01:07:07,320
Give up?

678
01:07:10,000 --> 01:07:12,520
Mercan is not something I can give up on.

679
01:07:14,000 --> 01:07:16,040
I have always gotten everything I wanted.

680
01:07:17,440 --> 01:07:18,440
Besides...

681
01:07:19,120 --> 01:07:20,720
Ateş and her have no future.

682
01:07:23,160 --> 01:07:26,160
I'm more certain than ever that
Mercan and I will be together.

683
01:07:29,000 --> 01:07:30,000
Yes...

684
01:07:30,320 --> 01:07:33,280
After what happened in their past,
those two can't be a thing anymore.

685
01:07:34,200 --> 01:07:35,200
They can't be.

686
01:07:35,640 --> 01:07:39,200
But still, Mercan won't say
yes to your offer of help...

687
01:07:42,920 --> 01:07:44,040
We won't know until we try.

688
01:08:04,560 --> 01:08:05,600
Enjoy your meal.

689
01:08:06,080 --> 01:08:07,080
Thanks...

690
01:08:33,160 --> 01:08:35,240
I'm one of the reasons for your pain.

691
01:08:39,160 --> 01:08:40,160
I know.

692
01:08:41,800 --> 01:08:43,680
I mean, I'm the daughter
of that man after all.

693
01:08:48,360 --> 01:08:50,080
I believe in us, Ateş.

694
01:08:54,280 --> 01:08:56,520
More than I believe in anything...

695
01:09:00,480 --> 01:09:01,920
There's one more thing I believe in.

696
01:09:04,680 --> 01:09:06,280
If we go back to how we were

697
01:09:07,200 --> 01:09:08,880
if you hold my hand

698
01:09:09,640 --> 01:09:11,800
we can face everything together.

699
01:09:12,760 --> 01:09:14,760
They can't destroy us.

700
01:09:15,920 --> 01:09:20,160
Neither my mom nor my dad...
nor the lies... nor our past.

701
01:09:28,040 --> 01:09:29,040
Eylül...

702
01:09:31,040 --> 01:09:33,520
I am so sorry for what my father did.

703
01:09:34,880 --> 01:09:36,600
For locking you up in there...

704
01:09:37,880 --> 01:09:39,360
For the pain he caused...

705
01:09:40,640 --> 01:09:45,520
For your fears... I am so sorry for
what you went through at a young age.

706
01:09:49,120 --> 01:09:50,120
Mercan

707
01:09:54,520 --> 01:09:57,360
After everything we've been
through, our love deserves this.

708
01:10:03,080 --> 01:10:04,960
Your heart says the same thing too, right?

709
01:10:09,560 --> 01:10:11,120
Your heart also tells you to choose us.

710
01:10:12,040 --> 01:10:13,960
-We can get through... -Mercan!

711
01:10:27,040 --> 01:10:28,280
We cannot be together.

712
01:10:34,440 --> 01:10:35,720
This love must end now.

713
01:10:41,000 --> 01:10:42,000
You were right.

714
01:10:45,520 --> 01:10:46,680
It won't work out between us.

715
01:11:19,600 --> 01:11:20,600
You were right.

716
01:11:24,040 --> 01:11:25,200
It won't work out between us.

717
01:12:24,040 --> 01:12:26,240
What do you mean?

718
01:12:27,040 --> 01:12:28,200
What does this mean?

719
01:12:29,120 --> 01:12:30,360
You know exactly what it means.

720
01:12:31,800 --> 01:12:36,520
No, no I don't.

721
01:12:37,000 --> 01:12:38,160
Tell me plainly.

722
01:12:38,560 --> 01:12:40,360
I want to hear what you have to say.

723
01:12:40,760 --> 01:12:41,960
There's nothing to question.

724
01:12:44,440 --> 01:12:45,800
This relationship cannot continue.

725
01:12:46,520 --> 01:12:48,480
This relationship cannot continue, huh?

726
01:12:49,640 --> 01:12:52,000
You... you must be joking?

727
01:12:53,200 --> 01:12:56,160
After days of saying you
loved me despite everything,

728
01:12:56,840 --> 01:12:58,840
and that you didn't want to break up...

729
01:12:59,640 --> 01:13:00,640
Mercan, please...

730
01:13:00,800 --> 01:13:01,840
Please what?

731
01:13:02,520 --> 01:13:05,440
I ran away from you when
I learned the truth...

732
01:13:06,480 --> 01:13:08,720
What did you do? You chased after me.

733
01:13:09,600 --> 01:13:12,080
You begged me to believe in your love…

734
01:13:13,280 --> 01:13:14,560
Now you stand before me...

735
01:13:16,040 --> 01:13:20,440
No, no... There must be something else.

736
01:13:21,160 --> 01:13:22,880
There's definitely something else going on.

737
01:13:24,160 --> 01:13:25,240
There is nothing else.

738
01:13:26,440 --> 01:13:28,480
I told you I wouldn't
give up on my revenge.

739
01:13:30,280 --> 01:13:31,680
It was just never meant to be.

740
01:13:32,880 --> 01:13:34,280
It's best to end it now.

741
01:13:35,480 --> 01:13:36,480
But...

742
01:13:37,320 --> 01:13:39,600
But you said you wouldn't
give up on your love either.

743
01:13:42,680 --> 01:13:44,000
I know you now.

744
01:13:44,800 --> 01:13:47,000
There's definitely something
you're not telling me.

745
01:13:47,640 --> 01:13:50,600
What happened? Why did you
suddenly go back on your word?

746
01:13:51,720 --> 01:13:52,840
There's nothing to tell.

747
01:13:56,680 --> 01:13:57,680
Ateş.

748
01:13:58,080 --> 01:13:59,080
Ateş, please.

749
01:14:00,920 --> 01:14:01,960
I was unfair to you.

750
01:14:03,720 --> 01:14:04,720
It was a mistake.

751
01:14:07,840 --> 01:14:08,840
A mistake, huh?

752
01:14:12,880 --> 01:14:14,360
Tell me you don't love me then.

753
01:14:19,720 --> 01:14:20,720
Go on.

754
01:14:23,600 --> 01:14:24,640
You can't say it.

755
01:14:26,120 --> 01:14:27,360
Because you love me.

756
01:14:28,200 --> 01:14:29,320
And I love you too.

757
01:14:31,600 --> 01:14:33,840
Why don't we leave everything behind then?

758
01:14:34,680 --> 01:14:38,400
Why don't we forget the
past and build a new life?

759
01:14:40,600 --> 01:14:44,080
We can leave this place and
start fresh, just the two of us.

760
01:15:09,920 --> 01:15:11,880
Being away from home is
hard, my dear. Very hard.

761
01:15:13,120 --> 01:15:14,720
I told you this before.

762
01:15:16,640 --> 01:15:19,440
Oh, the things I've seen and been through.

763
01:15:20,720 --> 01:15:22,360
It's a mother's heart, after all.

764
01:15:23,160 --> 01:15:27,400
What mother would want her
daughter to share a fate like hers?

765
01:15:27,560 --> 01:15:29,760
I know, mother. Believe me, I know.

766
01:15:30,440 --> 01:15:32,720
You spent your whole life looking after us.

767
01:15:33,760 --> 01:15:36,480
You never complained
about it, not even once.

768
01:15:37,600 --> 01:15:39,720
You only ever wanted the best for us.

769
01:15:42,520 --> 01:15:48,040
You can build your child a throne,
but you cannot forge their destiny.

770
01:15:49,520 --> 01:15:51,160
And Malik is your destiny.

771
01:15:51,840 --> 01:15:53,080
I can see it.

772
01:15:54,360 --> 01:15:56,440
The way he looks at you...

773
01:15:57,040 --> 01:15:58,240
How much he loves you...

774
01:15:59,520 --> 01:16:01,480
But believe me, I see this too...

775
01:16:02,920 --> 01:16:05,560
His family will cause you a lot of trouble.

776
01:16:09,880 --> 01:16:13,200
Will you be able to withstand that?

777
01:16:14,840 --> 01:16:15,840
If you can...

778
01:16:17,160 --> 01:16:18,400
I'm with you.

779
01:16:22,360 --> 01:16:25,640
I would love for you to
stay with me, my daughter.

780
01:16:27,800 --> 01:16:29,480
But I know you'll be unhappy.

781
01:16:31,200 --> 01:16:34,240
How could I ever be
unhappy by your side, mother?

782
01:16:37,800 --> 01:16:41,240
You are the great plane tree
that we lean our backs on.

783
01:16:46,640 --> 01:16:48,040
Why are you two crying?

784
01:16:49,120 --> 01:16:50,160
Did something bad happen?

785
01:16:51,800 --> 01:16:54,040
You're really asking that?

786
01:16:54,800 --> 01:16:56,200
Berat married you...

787
01:16:56,560 --> 01:16:58,160
What could be worse than that?

788
01:16:58,440 --> 01:16:59,520
How tactless!

789
01:16:59,880 --> 01:17:01,840
I thought something truly
terrible had happened.

790
01:17:04,760 --> 01:17:07,880
Come on, come on, don't start again!

791
01:17:08,920 --> 01:17:10,240
But she's the one who started it!

792
01:17:10,520 --> 01:17:12,000
Say something to your daughter first.

793
01:17:12,360 --> 01:17:13,600
She keeps making snide remarks.

794
01:17:14,400 --> 01:17:16,200
Maybe because you deserve it?

795
01:17:16,320 --> 01:17:18,439
I know your intentions!

796
01:17:18,440 --> 01:17:19,640
And what are my intentions?

797
01:17:19,680 --> 01:17:21,400
You're jealous of our happiness!

798
01:17:21,600 --> 01:17:22,600
-Really? -Mm-hmm.

799
01:17:22,720 --> 01:17:25,879
You want to separate me from my
husband, but you won't succeed!

800
01:17:25,880 --> 01:17:26,520
Mm-hmm.

801
01:17:26,760 --> 01:17:28,960
Zehra, that's enough. Çiçek, quit it.

802
01:17:29,440 --> 01:17:32,720
Stop fighting and get
back to work. Come on.

803
01:17:49,760 --> 01:17:50,760
Were you here?

804
01:17:51,600 --> 01:17:53,240
I've been looking for you everywhere.

805
01:17:54,040 --> 01:17:55,880
I thought I'd hang out
in your room for a bit.

806
01:17:56,920 --> 01:17:58,360
You seem to be in high spirits.

807
01:18:00,120 --> 01:18:01,320
Of course I am.

808
01:18:02,160 --> 01:18:03,840
Ateş and Mercan have broken up.

809
01:18:08,120 --> 01:18:10,560
Hopefully, we'll be rid
of that Mercan for good.

810
01:18:11,160 --> 01:18:12,720
Then I'll be even happier.

811
01:18:15,200 --> 01:18:16,760
I hope so too, but...

812
01:18:17,920 --> 01:18:20,360
Don't you go thinking this
is an opportunity for yourself.

813
01:18:21,520 --> 01:18:23,480
And why shouldn't I?

814
01:18:24,560 --> 01:18:27,520
I'm telling you so you don't waste
your time chasing a hopeless love.

815
01:18:28,800 --> 01:18:30,440
Why should it be hopeless?

816
01:18:30,840 --> 01:18:31,960
They've broken up.

817
01:18:34,040 --> 01:18:36,680
Even if they split, Ateş
won't turn and look at you.

818
01:18:37,160 --> 01:18:38,560
He's madly in love with that girl!

819
01:18:41,000 --> 01:18:42,000
Don't you dare, mother!

820
01:18:42,920 --> 01:18:45,920
Don't you ever tell me Ateş
is in love with Mercan again!

821
01:18:46,920 --> 01:18:48,520
Are you trying to drive me crazy?

822
01:18:49,000 --> 01:18:50,880
Don't you want me to be happy?

823
01:18:51,720 --> 01:18:53,560
Why won't you support me?

824
01:18:54,440 --> 01:18:56,320
Enough already! Get your head together!

825
01:18:56,800 --> 01:18:59,000
Why pin your hopes on
something that will never happen?

826
01:19:01,680 --> 01:19:04,440
If you love me even a
little, you'll stand by me.

827
01:19:05,920 --> 01:19:08,039
If I can't have Ateş, I'll kill my...

828
01:19:08,040 --> 01:19:09,040
Aslı!

829
01:19:12,520 --> 01:19:13,520
That's enough!

830
01:19:13,960 --> 01:19:18,120
After everything is over,
Ateş... will never be the same.

831
01:19:18,560 --> 01:19:19,920
You are still very young.

832
01:19:20,960 --> 01:19:23,296
When the time comes, you'll
fall in love with someone else.

833
01:19:23,320 --> 01:19:24,320
You'll start a family…

834
01:19:25,800 --> 01:19:29,480
But not with Ateş. I won't allow it.

835
01:19:42,200 --> 01:19:43,600
(sobs)

836
01:19:46,560 --> 01:19:48,320
Alright… Thank you so much.

837
01:19:55,600 --> 01:19:56,760
I was just coming to see you.

838
01:19:57,560 --> 01:19:58,560
What happened?

839
01:20:00,480 --> 01:20:03,640
The doctor who operated on
Mercan and Eylül has died.

840
01:20:05,240 --> 01:20:08,320
He had already been barred from the
profession for ties to organ trafficking.

841
01:20:09,040 --> 01:20:10,040
He even served time.

842
01:20:13,000 --> 01:20:14,000
Scumbag…

843
01:20:15,160 --> 01:20:17,280
Who knows how many lives
he snuffed out like Eylül's…

844
01:20:18,960 --> 01:20:22,480
I wish he hadn't died so we could have
beaten the life out of him ourselves...

845
01:20:23,800 --> 01:20:25,720
How can a person be so heartless?

846
01:20:26,200 --> 01:20:28,360
They don't care about
the lives they've ended.

847
01:20:28,560 --> 01:20:29,560
Ateş. Don't.

848
01:20:29,960 --> 01:20:31,400
Don't fall into Haydar’s trap.

849
01:20:32,160 --> 01:20:33,880
He's provoking you.

850
01:20:34,680 --> 01:20:36,000
You're not the old Tahir anymore.

851
01:20:36,600 --> 01:20:39,039
You're not that helpless, orphaned boy.

852
01:20:39,040 --> 01:20:41,160
You're an enemy more
powerful than he can handle.

853
01:20:42,280 --> 01:20:44,200
Sooner or later, he will
pay for what he's done.

854
01:20:45,480 --> 01:20:47,520
He will be his own grim reaper.

855
01:20:49,560 --> 01:20:50,560
What about Mercan?

856
01:20:51,000 --> 01:20:52,040
Are you going to tell her?

857
01:20:57,520 --> 01:20:58,520
I don't know, Cemal.

858
01:21:07,400 --> 01:21:09,160
I don't know what to do either.

859
01:21:12,720 --> 01:21:14,160
Mercan won't be able to handle this.

860
01:21:16,760 --> 01:21:19,640
Every time I look at Mercan, I
want to get away as fast as I can.

861
01:21:23,720 --> 01:21:25,720
On the other hand, I never
want to leave her side.

862
01:21:36,200 --> 01:21:37,200
On one side, my love...

863
01:21:40,320 --> 01:21:41,320
and on the other...

864
01:21:42,920 --> 01:21:44,520
Eylül and everything I've lived through.

865
01:21:49,440 --> 01:21:51,040
Wherever I turn, it's a burning fire.

866
01:22:07,000 --> 01:22:08,000
Oh, Ateş.

867
01:22:09,720 --> 01:22:11,920
You calculated everything.

868
01:22:13,880 --> 01:22:15,160
But you didn't account for love.

869
01:23:33,240 --> 01:23:36,160
You dropped a bomb on me and then
left as if you were running away.

870
01:23:37,600 --> 01:23:38,600
I wasn't running…

871
01:23:40,000 --> 01:23:41,480
There was nothing left to say.

872
01:23:43,480 --> 01:23:44,800
Nothing left, really?

873
01:23:45,240 --> 01:23:46,520
I think there is.

874
01:23:47,680 --> 01:23:49,456
Are we going to talk
about the same things again?

875
01:23:49,480 --> 01:23:50,560
If necessary, yes.

876
01:23:51,040 --> 01:23:52,559
You have to explain to me why

877
01:23:52,560 --> 01:23:54,480
you're talking about
breaking up out of nowhere.

878
01:23:55,880 --> 01:23:56,440
I don't.

879
01:23:56,880 --> 01:23:58,360
I made a mistake, that's all.

880
01:23:58,800 --> 01:24:00,640
I pushed you, knowing it wouldn't work.

881
01:24:02,120 --> 01:24:04,240
Our paths were going to
cross sooner or later anyway.

882
01:24:04,920 --> 01:24:06,680
It's best not to drag it out.

883
01:24:11,480 --> 01:24:13,320
It's so obvious that you're lying.

884
01:24:14,200 --> 01:24:16,600
You knew who I was from the very beginning!

885
01:24:17,440 --> 01:24:18,879
You married me knowingly,

886
01:24:18,880 --> 01:24:20,280
you fell in love with me knowingly!

887
01:24:22,720 --> 01:24:24,320
Don't push me any further, Mercan…

888
01:24:25,520 --> 01:24:27,800
I admit my mistake, what
more do you want me to do?

889
01:24:31,080 --> 01:24:33,480
When the hundred and eighty-seven
days are up, I'm leaving.

890
01:24:35,280 --> 01:24:36,400
It'll be over and done with.

891
01:24:37,120 --> 01:24:38,440
Over and done with, huh?

892
01:24:40,480 --> 01:24:41,480
Yes.

893
01:24:42,040 --> 01:24:43,240
We'll share the same room

894
01:24:43,520 --> 01:24:46,080
and do whatever is
required by the contract.

895
01:24:47,560 --> 01:24:48,560
Wow.

896
01:24:49,800 --> 01:24:51,400
I'm not following the contract.

897
01:24:53,360 --> 01:24:54,880
Force me, if you think it's that easy.

898
01:25:02,800 --> 01:25:03,840
Don't provoke me.

899
01:25:04,760 --> 01:25:05,920
I don't care.

900
01:25:07,680 --> 01:25:09,040
We made a deal

901
01:25:09,840 --> 01:25:11,160
and you have to stick to it.

902
01:25:14,760 --> 01:25:15,760
I don't want to talk.

903
01:25:17,840 --> 01:25:18,880
I've made my decision.

904
01:25:20,560 --> 01:25:21,800
You've made your decision?

905
01:25:21,840 --> 01:25:22,840
Is that so?

906
01:25:25,280 --> 01:25:26,520
I'm not your toy!

907
01:25:28,040 --> 01:25:30,440
You can't get close one day
and run away from me the next.

908
01:25:31,640 --> 01:25:33,200
If you have even an ounce of courage,

909
01:25:33,840 --> 01:25:35,200
you'll tell me what's going on!

910
01:25:35,800 --> 01:25:37,520
You owe me that much!

911
01:25:38,120 --> 01:25:39,400
What do you want me to tell you?

912
01:25:40,440 --> 01:25:42,800
Can't you see that it's
impossible for us to be together?

913
01:25:48,840 --> 01:25:50,720
You are the daughter of my sworn enemy!

914
01:25:58,000 --> 01:26:00,480
Don't you ever turn your back
on me while we're arguing again!

915
01:26:06,480 --> 01:26:08,000
Have you lost your mind?!

916
01:26:08,080 --> 01:26:09,080
Yes, I have.

917
01:26:09,360 --> 01:26:10,480
-Mercan! -Let go! Let go.

918
01:26:27,560 --> 01:26:29,360
I told you what you needed to know!

919
01:26:31,600 --> 01:26:32,600
Don't drag this out!

920
01:26:37,800 --> 01:26:38,800
Fine.

921
01:26:40,840 --> 01:26:41,840
I won't.

922
01:26:43,840 --> 01:26:45,080
You're right, it was a mistake…

923
01:26:47,640 --> 01:26:49,360
A massive mistake at that.

924
01:27:16,000 --> 01:27:18,240
You knew who I was from the very beginning!

925
01:27:19,160 --> 01:27:21,800
You married me knowingly, you
fell in love with me knowingly!

926
01:27:37,960 --> 01:27:40,120
I guess you're disappointed
to see me instead of Ateş.

927
01:27:42,320 --> 01:27:44,120
What are you doing at Ateş’s desk?

928
01:27:45,320 --> 01:27:46,440
Checking the contracts.

929
01:27:47,560 --> 01:27:51,400
Let's see if there's anything
else overlooked or ignored.

930
01:27:53,200 --> 01:27:54,280
You're going to check them?

931
01:27:54,680 --> 01:27:56,960
What would you know about legal contracts?

932
01:28:02,080 --> 01:28:03,600
You're mistaken, Aslı.

933
01:28:04,240 --> 01:28:06,760
I may not be a lawyer,
but I'm not an idiot.

934
01:28:08,280 --> 01:28:10,120
At the very least, I
can recognize signatures.

935
01:28:15,800 --> 01:28:18,000
You've become very touchy lately, Cemal.

936
01:28:19,400 --> 01:28:21,160
In fact, I'm the one
who should be offended…

937
01:28:22,840 --> 01:28:25,120
You're acting as if
I'm betraying my family.

938
01:28:26,520 --> 01:28:27,520
Haven't you?

939
01:28:28,800 --> 01:28:29,480
My intention...

940
01:28:29,481 --> 01:28:31,880
I know exactly what your intention is.

941
01:28:33,760 --> 01:28:35,000
Don't waste my time with words.

942
01:28:35,840 --> 01:28:38,320
I already deeply regret
not telling Ateş about Nezir.

943
01:28:38,360 --> 01:28:39,360
It's eating me alive.

944
01:28:39,520 --> 01:28:41,080
Cemal, please don't tell him.

945
01:28:41,320 --> 01:28:42,720
I'm begging you.

946
01:28:42,760 --> 01:28:44,199
Don't ruin things between us. Please.

947
01:28:44,200 --> 01:28:45,960
Aslı, get your head together!

948
01:28:47,040 --> 01:28:48,920
The man is madly in love with Mercan!

949
01:28:50,080 --> 01:28:51,776
He will never love another
woman in his entire life.

950
01:28:51,800 --> 01:28:52,800
Understand that already.

951
01:28:54,320 --> 01:28:55,600
Eventually, he will forget.

952
01:28:56,280 --> 01:28:58,120
And when he does, I'll
be the one by his side.

953
01:28:58,560 --> 01:29:02,320
Neither you nor my mother
can talk me out of this love.

954
01:29:03,040 --> 01:29:05,720
Ateş will realize eventually
that he will be happy with me.

955
01:29:06,920 --> 01:29:08,400
My love is enough for both of us.

956
01:29:08,560 --> 01:29:09,560
Love?

957
01:29:09,760 --> 01:29:10,840
Is that what you call love?

958
01:29:12,280 --> 01:29:15,720
If you truly loved him, you wouldn't
collaborate with Ateş’s enemy.

959
01:29:17,640 --> 01:29:20,960
Ateş loves someone else.
You know that very well.

960
01:29:22,560 --> 01:29:26,000
If he loves someone else, you would
have stepped aside so he could be happy.

961
01:29:31,240 --> 01:29:32,760
Yours isn't love.

962
01:29:38,080 --> 01:29:39,400
It's just a cheap obsession.

963
01:30:09,560 --> 01:30:11,360
I've cleaned the upstairs rooms, mother.

964
01:30:12,880 --> 01:30:14,280
Alright, dear. Thank you.

965
01:30:14,880 --> 01:30:17,280
When no one is around, give
the living room a once-over too.

966
01:30:18,360 --> 01:30:19,360
Will do.

967
01:30:21,040 --> 01:30:22,040
Oh, Lord.

968
01:30:25,200 --> 01:30:26,200
Hello.

969
01:30:27,000 --> 01:30:27,720
What is this?

970
01:30:28,000 --> 01:30:29,240
Did something bad happen?

971
01:30:29,280 --> 01:30:30,800
What's with the look on your face? No.

972
01:30:30,960 --> 01:30:32,160
No, quite the opposite.

973
01:30:32,800 --> 01:30:34,600
The deportation order
hasn't been issued yet.

974
01:30:35,480 --> 01:30:37,520
Oh! Thank God.

975
01:30:41,760 --> 01:30:43,360
Well, that's a good thing.

976
01:30:44,200 --> 01:30:46,120
Sure, it's good.

977
01:30:46,520 --> 01:30:50,080
But if I can't complete the
missing documents within 24 hours,

978
01:30:50,200 --> 01:30:51,360
that's when I'll be deported.

979
01:30:53,200 --> 01:30:56,159
It's not a problem, we'll
handle whatever is missing.

980
01:30:56,160 --> 01:30:56,880
Yes, that's right.

981
01:30:57,120 --> 01:30:59,800
Mr. Haydar was a bit negligent.

982
01:31:00,440 --> 01:31:01,160
(indistinct line)

983
01:31:01,440 --> 01:31:03,920
There's nothing to worry about here.

984
01:31:04,280 --> 01:31:07,400
Talk to Mr. Ateş
immediately, he'll handle it.

985
01:31:08,000 --> 01:31:09,960
I spoke with Cemal and
explained the situation.

986
01:31:10,240 --> 01:31:13,600
Thankfully, there are some
documents he requested from me.

987
01:31:16,880 --> 01:31:17,960
Oh, that's good then.

988
01:31:18,360 --> 01:31:20,680
I hope everything works out for you, son.

989
01:31:20,720 --> 01:31:21,400
I hope so.

990
01:31:21,480 --> 01:31:24,640
Make sure everything is ready
so nothing is missing this time.

991
01:31:25,880 --> 01:31:31,720
Yes, yes. I'll start preparing
the documents right away.

992
01:31:31,840 --> 01:31:32,840
Okay.

993
01:31:33,160 --> 01:31:34,880
-We'll handle it. -See you.

994
01:31:38,200 --> 01:31:39,200
Come here, come on.

995
01:31:39,880 --> 01:31:41,360
My dear.

996
01:31:41,680 --> 01:31:42,680
He loves me very much.

997
01:31:44,680 --> 01:31:45,936
Always keep smiling
like this. Don't be sad.

998
01:31:45,960 --> 01:31:47,080
Alright.

999
01:31:56,960 --> 01:31:58,320
"Don't drag it out," huh?

1000
01:31:59,680 --> 01:32:01,200
I won't.

1001
01:32:01,440 --> 01:32:02,880
May Mr. Ateş be happy.

1002
01:32:23,200 --> 01:32:24,200
You scared me.

1003
01:32:25,240 --> 01:32:26,240
I'm sorry.

1004
01:32:30,080 --> 01:32:32,280
Leave it, I'll handle it.

1005
01:32:33,640 --> 01:32:34,640
There's no need!

1006
01:32:35,440 --> 01:32:36,880
I dropped it, I'll pick it up.

1007
01:32:37,800 --> 01:32:38,800
I said I'll do it.

1008
01:32:40,240 --> 01:32:41,360
You'll cut your hand.

1009
01:32:43,880 --> 01:32:45,040
And I said there's no need!

1010
01:32:45,840 --> 01:32:48,680
If I cut it, I cut it.
It's my hand. You leave it.

1011
01:33:27,880 --> 01:33:28,880
Listen to me for once!

1012
01:33:31,480 --> 01:33:32,920
I don't want to listen.

1013
01:33:38,720 --> 01:33:39,960
I broke it, I'll pick it up!

1014
01:33:40,560 --> 01:33:41,640
I'm not like you!

1015
01:33:45,360 --> 01:33:46,440
What are you trying to say?

1016
01:33:49,360 --> 01:33:52,600
I mean I don't break things
and then just turn my back!

1017
01:34:20,800 --> 01:34:23,720
Whenever we enter the kitchen
together, we break things.

1018
01:34:37,560 --> 01:34:39,000
Don't drive me crazy any further!

1019
01:34:39,240 --> 01:34:40,600
Give me a proper answer already!

1020
01:34:41,200 --> 01:34:42,600
Don't mess with my heartbeat.

1021
01:34:43,440 --> 01:34:45,000
This is the language you understand.

1022
01:34:45,360 --> 01:34:46,640
Breaking and destroying.

1023
01:34:47,040 --> 01:34:48,560
Fine, if this is what you want...

1024
01:34:49,880 --> 01:34:51,640
If this is what you understand.

1025
01:34:52,040 --> 01:34:53,040
There!

1026
01:34:53,480 --> 01:34:56,520
What are you doing! Stop! Stop, I said!

1027
01:34:57,560 --> 01:34:58,680
Stop, I'm telling you.

1028
01:34:58,720 --> 01:34:59,720
Mercan, stop.

1029
01:35:07,120 --> 01:35:10,800
I won't let go of you anymore.
Because I know you love me too.

1030
01:35:12,320 --> 01:35:13,320
I don't love you.

1031
01:35:13,640 --> 01:35:15,799
You do. You're dying for me.

1032
01:35:15,800 --> 01:35:16,919
I said I don't love you.

1033
01:35:16,920 --> 01:35:17,920
You do. I don't.

1034
01:35:18,400 --> 01:35:19,639
Admit it, you love me.

1035
01:35:19,640 --> 01:35:20,839
I said I don't!

1036
01:35:20,840 --> 01:35:21,480
You love me!

1037
01:35:21,481 --> 01:35:22,800
I love you so much.

1038
01:35:24,760 --> 01:35:26,760
So much... Truly so much.

1039
01:35:29,880 --> 01:35:30,880
You...

1040
01:35:32,520 --> 01:35:35,800
You are the fire. And I
am the wind to that fire.

1041
01:35:37,680 --> 01:35:39,760
Even though I try to
erase you from my mind,

1042
01:35:39,920 --> 01:35:41,680
I couldn't cast you out of my heart.

1043
01:35:48,960 --> 01:35:51,240
When the wind finds the
fire, it becomes immortal.

1044
01:35:52,920 --> 01:35:54,560
Our love is immortal like that.

1045
01:35:58,840 --> 01:36:01,800
Maybe this is a sign that we
shouldn't enter the kitchen together.

1046
01:36:08,040 --> 01:36:10,600
Maybe it's a sign that we
shouldn't do anything at all.

1047
01:36:12,440 --> 01:36:14,720
We were supposed to be like
this from the start anyway.

1048
01:36:15,640 --> 01:36:16,640
Yes.

1049
01:36:18,000 --> 01:36:19,000
Thankfully, it's over.

1050
01:36:20,720 --> 01:36:22,600
Even if a bit late, we did the right thing.

1051
01:36:23,360 --> 01:36:24,360
Isn't it nice?

1052
01:36:25,480 --> 01:36:28,320
Whenever you feel like it, you force
yourself into someone else's life.

1053
01:36:29,720 --> 01:36:33,120
And then you say, "Oops, I
made a mistake, I'm leaving."

1054
01:36:36,160 --> 01:36:37,160
Mercan, I...

1055
01:36:41,920 --> 01:36:42,920
I'm sorry.

1056
01:36:43,120 --> 01:36:44,480
-I didn't want it to be— -Don't!

1057
01:36:45,800 --> 01:36:47,240
Don't you dare pity me!

1058
01:36:48,880 --> 01:36:55,040
I don't need anyone's pity,
especially yours. Do you hear me?

1059
01:36:55,840 --> 01:36:57,760
What I feel for you is simply...

1060
01:37:05,840 --> 01:37:07,080
I respect you.

1061
01:37:10,680 --> 01:37:12,360
You don't respect anything.

1062
01:37:13,920 --> 01:37:17,600
You don't even care about
what you've burned and broken!

1063
01:37:19,440 --> 01:37:20,600
I picked up the pieces.

1064
01:37:24,120 --> 01:37:25,120
Yes, you did.

1065
01:37:26,160 --> 01:37:27,720
And you threw them all in the trash.

1066
01:37:32,920 --> 01:37:34,560
Because you can't put them back together.

1067
01:38:22,960 --> 01:38:24,680
Mercan bought it for him on his birthday.

1068
01:38:38,800 --> 01:38:40,080
What are you doing here?

1069
01:38:42,720 --> 01:38:43,720
This was my son's.

1070
01:38:46,200 --> 01:38:47,360
Just like this room.

1071
01:38:53,160 --> 01:38:54,360
Besides... This is my house!

1072
01:38:56,280 --> 01:38:58,400
I enter wherever I want!

1073
01:38:59,040 --> 01:39:00,080
This is my house too!

1074
01:39:00,760 --> 01:39:02,280
I am Haydar Yıldırım's son.

1075
01:39:03,120 --> 01:39:04,920
I have as much right
to everything as you do!

1076
01:39:08,440 --> 01:39:11,160
I knew what kind of person you
were the moment I first saw you.

1077
01:39:12,440 --> 01:39:15,240
You're a greedy, calculating sneak…

1078
01:39:15,920 --> 01:39:17,600
Get this into your head.

1079
01:39:18,200 --> 01:39:21,240
Haydar Yıldırım had one son.

1080
01:39:25,440 --> 01:39:28,040
And that's my son, Murat.

1081
01:39:31,680 --> 01:39:34,560
Don't you ever think
you can take his place.

1082
01:39:37,360 --> 01:39:38,720
I wouldn't want to take his place.

1083
01:39:41,000 --> 01:39:42,400
He was a murderer.

1084
01:39:47,160 --> 01:39:49,960
Who are you to speak of my son?

1085
01:39:54,920 --> 01:39:55,920
Don't you dare!

1086
01:39:57,520 --> 01:40:00,800
Your mother was a lowly woman
who slept with married men!

1087
01:40:02,120 --> 01:40:04,360
You're in no position
to look down on anyone!

1088
01:40:04,880 --> 01:40:06,920
My mother ran away because of you!

1089
01:40:08,640 --> 01:40:10,840
You keep telling yourself that!

1090
01:40:30,680 --> 01:40:32,040
I wouldn't want to take his place.

1091
01:40:32,920 --> 01:40:34,240
He was a murderer.

1092
01:40:39,040 --> 01:40:40,040
Malik!

1093
01:40:40,960 --> 01:40:43,960
What are you doing here, dear? You
were supposed to prepare your documents…

1094
01:40:44,800 --> 01:40:47,680
I can't find my passport, Çiçek.
I've looked everywhere, it's gone.

1095
01:40:48,120 --> 01:40:49,720
Alright, we'll find it, calm down…

1096
01:40:50,480 --> 01:40:52,840
Let me have a look
too. Maybe you missed it.

1097
01:40:53,000 --> 01:40:55,280
I've looked everywhere twice.

1098
01:40:55,520 --> 01:40:58,960
Maybe… I don't know… I thought it might
have stayed in the car, so I came here.

1099
01:40:59,240 --> 01:41:01,240
What would your passport
be doing in the car?

1100
01:41:01,760 --> 01:41:05,960
I don't know. Maybe I took
it with me, maybe it fell out…

1101
01:41:06,000 --> 01:41:07,200
I'm just looking around.

1102
01:41:07,440 --> 01:41:09,320
I just can't remember where I put it.

1103
01:41:09,920 --> 01:41:13,800
Time is running out, but
panicking will only make it worse.

1104
01:41:13,840 --> 01:41:18,240
You look around here, and I'll
search your room one more time.

1105
01:41:18,320 --> 01:41:19,880
Maybe we missed it.

1106
01:41:20,080 --> 01:41:21,080
Okay. Okay.

1107
01:41:27,920 --> 01:41:29,360
I went to the mosque the other day.

1108
01:41:29,600 --> 01:41:31,560
I wonder if I dropped it there?

1109
01:41:34,360 --> 01:41:36,720
I'd better go and have a look.

1110
01:41:52,480 --> 01:41:53,760
Thankfully, it's over.

1111
01:41:53,960 --> 01:41:55,880
Even if a bit late, we did the right thing.

1112
01:41:56,520 --> 01:41:57,520
I won't cry.

1113
01:42:00,440 --> 01:42:01,440
I won't cry.

1114
01:42:28,480 --> 01:42:29,600
How are you, Mercan?

1115
01:42:32,240 --> 01:42:33,600
I'm fine, thanks.

1116
01:42:34,840 --> 01:42:36,200
Can we talk for a bit?

1117
01:42:36,960 --> 01:42:37,960
About what?

1118
01:42:39,800 --> 01:42:41,400
You know we can't talk comfortably here.

1119
01:42:42,360 --> 01:42:43,360
Shall we go outside?

1120
01:42:44,600 --> 01:42:47,840
No, Nezir. Whatever you
have to say, say it here.

1121
01:42:48,320 --> 01:42:50,680
Mercan, you know he
won't let us talk freely.

1122
01:42:51,920 --> 01:42:53,840
We'll sit by the shore for a while.

1123
01:42:54,640 --> 01:42:57,120
I promise, I won't keep you
long. I'll bring you right back.

1124
01:43:21,120 --> 01:43:22,640
Alright. But I can't stay long.

1125
01:43:23,080 --> 01:43:24,080
I promise.

1126
01:43:58,840 --> 01:43:59,840
Mercan!

1127
01:44:05,520 --> 01:44:07,560
Don't do this to me!

1128
01:45:01,320 --> 01:45:03,200
I brought you something to eat.

1129
01:45:32,200 --> 01:45:33,200
Mr. Haydar…

1130
01:45:35,200 --> 01:45:37,360
It's not my place, but...

1131
01:45:37,480 --> 01:45:39,680
Since the past has been
laid bare like this…

1132
01:45:40,000 --> 01:45:42,040
Isn't it time you told the truth?

1133
01:45:51,080 --> 01:45:53,680
Don't you dare, Binnaz… Don't you dare!

1134
01:45:56,600 --> 01:45:58,680
How much longer are we
going to carry this burden?

1135
01:45:58,840 --> 01:46:01,040
I need that secret.

1136
01:46:02,160 --> 01:46:05,880
If they find out, I'll make you
pay for it once I'm out of here.

1137
01:46:09,440 --> 01:46:10,680
And you know I will.

1138
01:46:21,000 --> 01:46:22,000
Come on, Mrs. Binnaz.

1139
01:47:08,640 --> 01:47:10,960
I'm listening.

1140
01:47:12,080 --> 01:47:13,400
Mercan, my heart is not at ease.

1141
01:47:15,120 --> 01:47:16,360
You don't accept it, but...

1142
01:47:16,600 --> 01:47:19,240
Nezir, we've discussed this before?

1143
01:47:21,040 --> 01:47:22,040
I know...

1144
01:47:23,640 --> 01:47:25,120
But I can't help it, what can I do...

1145
01:47:27,160 --> 01:47:28,760
All I care about is your safety.

1146
01:47:30,160 --> 01:47:31,760
It's clear what they did to your father.

1147
01:47:31,960 --> 01:47:33,680
Next, it'll be your and your mother's turn.

1148
01:47:34,320 --> 01:47:35,320
Please, Nezir.

1149
01:47:37,240 --> 01:47:39,040
Mercan, these people are dangerous.

1150
01:47:40,760 --> 01:47:43,040
They've come here with a
grudge they've held for years.

1151
01:47:43,680 --> 01:47:45,680
It's not right for you
to stay here with them.

1152
01:47:47,240 --> 01:47:50,240
Let me protect you.

1153
01:47:50,880 --> 01:47:53,280
I don't need anyone to protect me.

1154
01:47:53,960 --> 01:47:55,000
Especially not from Ateş.

1155
01:47:58,280 --> 01:47:59,680
He won't hurt me.

1156
01:47:59,840 --> 01:48:01,240
He won't hurt anyone.

1157
01:48:04,840 --> 01:48:07,120
Mercan, my feelings for
you have never changed.

1158
01:48:07,680 --> 01:48:08,920
-When you're with me— -Nezir.

1159
01:48:10,240 --> 01:48:11,240
Please.

1160
01:48:14,880 --> 01:48:16,160
Mercan, please listen.

1161
01:48:17,000 --> 01:48:19,480
I don't know if I'll ever have
an opportunity like this again.

1162
01:48:20,240 --> 01:48:21,600
One hundred and eighty-seven days.

1163
01:48:22,960 --> 01:48:25,000
After the hundred and
eighty-seven days are over...

1164
01:48:25,560 --> 01:48:26,680
Once you divorce that man...

1165
01:48:28,640 --> 01:48:29,640
Marry me.

1166
01:48:41,040 --> 01:48:43,160
I'm willing to settle for
even a single day with you.

1167
01:48:46,480 --> 01:48:47,960
Even just a single second.

1168
01:48:53,000 --> 01:48:55,480
My only concern is hearing your
voice, looking into your eyes.

1169
01:48:56,520 --> 01:48:58,120
I won't touch you unless you want me to.

1170
01:48:59,320 --> 01:49:02,120
I won't touch you until the day
I die, if that's what you want.

1171
01:49:06,040 --> 01:49:07,840
My only wish is to be
able to make you happy.

1172
01:49:12,000 --> 01:49:13,240
I'll come if you say come.

1173
01:49:13,720 --> 01:49:14,720
I'll go if you say go.

1174
01:49:17,960 --> 01:49:18,960
I'll die if you say die.

1175
01:49:21,400 --> 01:49:23,160
You're more precious
to me than my own life.

1176
01:49:25,120 --> 01:49:26,400
Once this business is over...

1177
01:49:28,680 --> 01:49:29,680
Marry me.

1178
01:49:42,480 --> 01:49:44,240
You know I love Ateş very much, Nezir.

1179
01:49:46,160 --> 01:49:48,480
How will you be happy with
someone who loves another?

1180
01:49:51,440 --> 01:49:53,721
And why should I step out of
one ordeal and into another?

1181
01:49:54,440 --> 01:49:56,360
Can't things be resolved without marriage?

1182
01:50:01,800 --> 01:50:03,280
Nothing is important to me.

1183
01:50:05,280 --> 01:50:07,600
Only you matter, Mercan.

1184
01:50:08,760 --> 01:50:09,760
Only you.

1185
01:50:11,520 --> 01:50:13,040
These hundred and eighty-seven days...

1186
01:50:14,200 --> 01:50:16,160
Marry me when you divorce.

1187
01:50:32,640 --> 01:50:33,640
Let me think about it.

1188
01:50:44,040 --> 01:50:45,200
What the hell are you saying?

1189
01:50:45,680 --> 01:50:47,760
What marriage after a
hundred and eighty-seven days?

1190
01:50:47,960 --> 01:50:50,400
I was telling her to marry
me once she gets rid of you.

1191
01:50:50,600 --> 01:50:52,280
Ateş, don't!

1192
01:50:53,480 --> 01:50:54,600
Ateş, calm down.

1193
01:50:57,360 --> 01:50:58,800
Our conversation was already over.

1194
01:50:59,480 --> 01:51:00,976
Talking was a mistake in the first place!

1195
01:51:01,000 --> 01:51:02,520
Why do you come here with this man?

1196
01:51:02,640 --> 01:51:04,000
And you say you'll think about it!

1197
01:51:04,920 --> 01:51:05,920
Ateş, calm down!

1198
01:51:06,200 --> 01:51:07,360
I won't calm down!

1199
01:51:07,920 --> 01:51:11,280
Look! I'm telling you,
Mercan! This man is dangerous.

1200
01:51:11,880 --> 01:51:13,160
Think about what I said.

1201
01:51:15,600 --> 01:51:16,640
In your dreams.

1202
01:51:18,440 --> 01:51:19,720
I won't leave her to anyone.

1203
01:51:21,080 --> 01:51:22,440
-Ateş! -Mercan!

1204
01:51:24,360 --> 01:51:28,480
I won't let you hurt her.

1205
01:51:30,960 --> 01:51:33,320
Who the hell are you
to think about my wife?

1206
01:51:36,280 --> 01:51:37,280
Nezir!

1207
01:51:38,120 --> 01:51:38,720
Don't you interfere!

1208
01:51:39,120 --> 01:51:40,160
I already have!

1209
01:51:40,840 --> 01:51:42,800
I won't leave you in this man's hands.

1210
01:52:01,480 --> 01:52:04,480
Enough! I'm sick of your fighting.

1211
01:52:04,520 --> 01:52:10,360
Enough already, I've had it!
Always fighting! What is this! Enough!

1212
01:52:11,360 --> 01:52:12,640
Whatever happens, happens.

1213
01:52:14,920 --> 01:52:15,920
Mercan!

1214
01:52:17,080 --> 01:52:19,160
Mercan!

1215
01:52:19,840 --> 01:52:21,120
Think about what I said, Mercan!

1216
01:52:23,120 --> 01:52:24,120
Mercan, wait!

1217
01:52:24,800 --> 01:52:25,800
What!

1218
01:52:26,120 --> 01:52:29,320
Why don't you say to my face what
you're going to think about, huh?

1219
01:52:29,800 --> 01:52:32,000
You heard perfectly well
what I'm going to think about.

1220
01:52:32,320 --> 01:52:33,720
Besides, what's it to you?

1221
01:52:34,000 --> 01:52:36,760
It is my business! You are still my wife!

1222
01:52:38,120 --> 01:52:41,400
Like you said, it's just a
marriage contract on paper!

1223
01:52:42,120 --> 01:52:43,560
And what are you questioning?

1224
01:52:44,520 --> 01:52:47,200
Nothing you say or do makes any sense!

1225
01:52:47,800 --> 01:52:49,680
You've been saying
"It's over" since morning.

1226
01:52:50,880 --> 01:52:53,800
But at the slightest thing,
you try to call me to account!

1227
01:52:54,680 --> 01:52:57,200
If we're just a contract to you,

1228
01:52:57,600 --> 01:53:00,560
why Nezir came or what he
said is none of your business!

1229
01:53:05,280 --> 01:53:07,080
Look, you're really
pushing your luck today!

1230
01:53:07,280 --> 01:53:09,400
Oh, really? I hadn't noticed.

1231
01:53:09,880 --> 01:53:11,240
Don't drive me crazy.

1232
01:53:11,760 --> 01:53:13,640
I don't even care if you go crazy or not.

1233
01:53:27,720 --> 01:53:28,720
Look at me!

1234
01:53:29,440 --> 01:53:30,440
What are you looking at?

1235
01:53:32,640 --> 01:53:33,640
Were you talking to me?

1236
01:53:33,680 --> 01:53:34,680
I was talking to you.

1237
01:53:34,920 --> 01:53:37,840
Do you like what you see that much?
Why are you looking at a married man?

1238
01:53:40,320 --> 01:53:42,280
Mercan, what are you doing? Come on.

1239
01:53:42,680 --> 01:53:43,680
I'm sorry.

1240
01:53:43,880 --> 01:53:46,240
What are you sorry for? It's
not like I did anything wrong!

1241
01:53:46,800 --> 01:53:49,800
Where are you going? Why don't
you tell me why you were looking!

1242
01:53:50,200 --> 01:53:52,240
Mercan, what are you doing?
Get a hold of yourself!

1243
01:53:52,320 --> 01:53:55,040
Why are you saying sorry? You
might as well have fallen at her feet!

1244
01:53:55,120 --> 01:53:56,840
Go chase after her, don't let her get away!

1245
01:53:56,920 --> 01:53:58,576
Mercan, what are you doing?
Get a hold of yourself!

1246
01:53:58,600 --> 01:54:01,800
I am myself! Who was that
woman? Why was she looking at you!

1247
01:54:02,080 --> 01:54:04,560
Mercan, you're being ridiculous.
How should I know who she is?

1248
01:54:06,680 --> 01:54:07,960
Quit it!

1249
01:54:08,160 --> 01:54:11,720
Oh, so when I do it, it's ridiculous,
but when you do it, it's normal.

1250
01:54:12,040 --> 01:54:13,679
Now do you see how it feels?

1251
01:54:13,680 --> 01:54:14,960
So you did it on purpose?

1252
01:54:15,040 --> 01:54:17,200
No! I didn't do it on purpose.

1253
01:54:17,800 --> 01:54:20,920
If you'd let me, I would've shown
her what it means to look at you.

1254
01:54:21,800 --> 01:54:22,800
Come on, move it.

1255
01:54:23,360 --> 01:54:24,960
Don't pull me. I can walk.

1256
01:54:25,800 --> 01:54:27,200
Were you jealous of me?

1257
01:54:28,840 --> 01:54:31,760
You would've seen real jealousy
if you'd looked back at that woman.

1258
01:54:33,760 --> 01:54:35,960
By the way, don't think
I've forgotten about Nezir.

1259
01:54:36,400 --> 01:54:37,400
Oh, don't you forget.

1260
01:54:37,760 --> 01:54:39,160
Still talking about Nezir.

1261
01:54:41,000 --> 01:54:42,440
So you're going to think about it...

1262
01:54:43,640 --> 01:54:44,640
You...

1263
01:54:45,360 --> 01:54:46,440
can't think...

1264
01:54:47,160 --> 01:54:48,520
of anything but me!

1265
01:55:17,040 --> 01:55:18,040
Welcome.

1266
01:55:18,520 --> 01:55:19,520
Good to be here.

1267
01:55:20,200 --> 01:55:22,240
Do you know if Mercan is around?

1268
01:55:22,880 --> 01:55:26,000
No. She left with
Nezir. Ateş is after them.

1269
01:55:26,240 --> 01:55:27,560
Oh, brother!

1270
01:55:28,440 --> 01:55:29,960
There's going to be trouble again.

1271
01:55:31,800 --> 01:55:34,880
Your brother likes to
cause trouble. Is that right?

1272
01:55:37,800 --> 01:55:42,800
Others create the problems, but for some reason,
it's always my brother who's "causing trouble"?

1273
01:55:44,600 --> 01:55:47,840
No one has had any peace since you arrived.

1274
01:55:49,480 --> 01:55:51,120
I don't understand you at all anyway!

1275
01:55:52,280 --> 01:55:56,160
Why are you so full of hate and anger?

1276
01:55:56,920 --> 01:55:58,200
I just don't get it.

1277
01:56:01,560 --> 01:56:04,280
If you knew what companionship on
a journey meant, you'd understand.

1278
01:56:06,200 --> 01:56:07,920
Then talk to your companion.

1279
01:56:08,760 --> 01:56:11,000
Tell him to stop making Mercan suffer.

1280
01:56:14,840 --> 01:56:18,480
Mercan fell for someone, fell
in love for the first time.

1281
01:56:19,560 --> 01:56:21,280
She doesn't deserve any of this.

1282
01:56:25,360 --> 01:56:26,360
What is it to you?

1283
01:56:27,240 --> 01:56:30,520
Why do you stick your nose into
things that are none of your business?

1284
01:56:31,280 --> 01:56:32,600
What do you want then?

1285
01:56:33,240 --> 01:56:34,920
Should everyone just kill each other?

1286
01:56:39,480 --> 01:56:40,480
Aslı, don't get involved.

1287
01:56:42,120 --> 01:56:43,120
I will get involved.

1288
01:56:43,520 --> 01:56:44,760
Don't drag it out, okay.

1289
01:56:48,160 --> 01:56:51,600
Don't mind Aslı… Her nerves
are a bit frayed lately.

1290
01:56:55,000 --> 01:56:56,000
It's not a problem…

1291
01:56:56,480 --> 01:56:57,840
She's always like this.

1292
01:57:01,480 --> 01:57:02,480
Sneaky.

1293
01:57:14,840 --> 01:57:15,840
Annoying.

1294
01:57:25,200 --> 01:57:26,200
Haydar?

1295
01:57:28,520 --> 01:57:29,520
Nermin?

1296
01:57:31,200 --> 01:57:32,400
I was wondering how you were.

1297
01:57:34,480 --> 01:57:35,960
How should I be, Nermin?

1298
01:57:36,920 --> 01:57:40,520
I'm about to lose my mind! Help me, Nermin.

1299
01:57:42,080 --> 01:57:43,800
Calm down, Haydar! Calm down!

1300
01:57:44,360 --> 01:57:45,680
What can we possibly do?

1301
01:57:46,600 --> 01:57:49,680
Look, your dear son is here too,
but he doesn't even care about you.

1302
01:57:52,360 --> 01:57:53,920
He's out enjoying himself.

1303
01:57:56,000 --> 01:57:57,400
I have you…

1304
01:57:58,200 --> 01:57:59,960
no one but you can help me.

1305
01:58:00,920 --> 01:58:03,680
Please, find a key or
something, do something, Nermin.

1306
01:58:04,040 --> 01:58:06,240
I have to get out of here.

1307
01:58:07,840 --> 01:58:08,840
Alright, alright.

1308
01:58:09,920 --> 01:58:11,560
I'll try to do something.

1309
01:58:13,200 --> 01:58:14,240
Hurry up.

1310
01:58:16,400 --> 01:58:17,520
Don't worry.

1311
01:58:51,200 --> 01:58:52,200
Hello?

1312
01:58:55,080 --> 01:58:56,080
One second. Mercan.

1313
01:58:57,600 --> 01:58:58,600
What!

1314
01:58:59,160 --> 01:59:00,200
Wait, we're going to talk.

1315
01:59:00,400 --> 01:59:01,400
I can't wait.

1316
01:59:07,160 --> 01:59:08,160
I'm listening.

1317
01:59:10,720 --> 01:59:13,840
Well, well. Are you coming
from a visit to your father?

1318
01:59:16,600 --> 01:59:18,480
How many times have I
told you not to touch me!

1319
01:59:18,880 --> 01:59:22,160
Just you wait, your turn will come
after your father's. Murderer's daughter!

1320
01:59:23,320 --> 01:59:26,000
I'm sick of your threats! Your lies.

1321
01:59:26,320 --> 01:59:28,360
What's a lie? Isn't your father a murderer?

1322
01:59:29,920 --> 01:59:31,880
You're as immoral as your father!

1323
01:59:31,960 --> 01:59:35,880
Even though your father killed
Eylül, you're still around Ateş.

1324
01:59:36,880 --> 01:59:38,960
If you had even an ounce of shame,

1325
01:59:39,200 --> 01:59:42,000
you'd bow your head
and stay away from Ateş!

1326
01:59:43,160 --> 01:59:44,736
You'd be ashamed to look him in the face!

1327
01:59:44,760 --> 01:59:45,760
Mrs. Müzeyyen!

1328
01:59:46,560 --> 01:59:47,760
Don't touch her! Let go, Ateş!

1329
01:59:48,320 --> 01:59:48,960
Don't you dare!

1330
01:59:49,280 --> 01:59:50,280
I said don't!

1331
01:59:50,640 --> 01:59:51,640
Don't touch her!

1332
01:59:57,000 --> 01:59:58,800
Are you alright? You're not hurt, are you?

1333
02:00:04,120 --> 02:00:05,120
Mrs. Müzeyyen!

1334
02:00:06,080 --> 02:00:07,760
Mercan is my wife!

1335
02:00:08,880 --> 02:00:09,880
My red line.

1336
02:00:10,520 --> 02:00:12,160
You crossed that red line.

1337
02:00:12,480 --> 02:00:13,840
I don't want to hear another word.

1338
02:00:14,640 --> 02:00:16,240
I've lost my trust in you now.

1339
02:00:17,560 --> 02:00:21,600
Know your place before
I lose my respect too!

1340
02:00:58,600 --> 02:00:59,600
My dear wife.

1341
02:01:00,520 --> 02:01:00,840
Hmm?

1342
02:01:00,960 --> 02:01:02,720
Would you pour some
tea for our mother? Huh?

1343
02:01:07,440 --> 02:01:08,520
Of course, my dear husband.

1344
02:01:08,720 --> 02:01:10,880
Let me pour some tea for our mother.

1345
02:01:10,920 --> 02:01:12,000
Come on, my dear wife.

1346
02:01:21,080 --> 02:01:22,080
Heh!

1347
02:01:26,560 --> 02:01:27,640
What happened?

1348
02:01:30,080 --> 02:01:30,680
What's the matter?

1349
02:01:31,000 --> 02:01:32,760
We couldn't find the passport.

1350
02:01:46,280 --> 02:01:47,360
What's going to happen now?

1351
02:01:47,920 --> 02:01:50,120
Believe me, I have no idea.

1352
02:01:52,920 --> 02:01:53,920
It's no problem.

1353
02:01:54,280 --> 02:01:55,880
There's no need to despair.

1354
02:01:56,000 --> 02:01:59,680
It'll turn up eventually. And
from the most unexpected place.

1355
02:01:59,920 --> 02:02:02,560
That's what I'm saying. We'll
find that passport eventually.

1356
02:02:04,000 --> 02:02:05,680
Can't Mr. Cemal do something?

1357
02:02:06,480 --> 02:02:11,160
I spoke with him, but... He said
he'd see if anything could be done.

1358
02:02:15,240 --> 02:02:16,240
Berat.

1359
02:02:17,360 --> 02:02:20,680
Since Malik is leaving,
let's move into his room.

1360
02:02:22,920 --> 02:02:24,360
Girl, are you doing this on purpose?

1361
02:02:29,920 --> 02:02:31,360
Is this the time, Zehra?

1362
02:02:31,840 --> 02:02:34,601
No, but if we know, at least we
can choose the furniture accordingly.

1363
02:02:35,560 --> 02:02:37,200
Look, you're really going too far.

1364
02:02:38,240 --> 02:02:40,040
And she calls me tactless.

1365
02:02:41,040 --> 02:02:42,400
Calm down.

1366
02:02:44,160 --> 02:02:45,440
For God's sake, keep quiet.

1367
02:02:46,600 --> 02:02:48,720
I want to drink my tea in peace.

1368
02:02:48,800 --> 02:02:50,160
I'm sick of your bickering.

1369
02:02:58,520 --> 02:02:59,520
Zehra.

1370
02:03:00,280 --> 02:03:04,640
Refresh the tea, come on. That's
what new brides do around here.

1371
02:03:05,720 --> 02:03:10,000
I guess your new brides are
brought in just for service then.

1372
02:03:30,560 --> 02:03:32,080
Thank God.

1373
02:03:33,160 --> 02:03:34,160
Enjoy your tea.

1374
02:03:34,240 --> 02:03:35,560
Thanks, Zehra. Thank you.

1375
02:03:35,600 --> 02:03:36,600
Well done, Zehra.

1376
02:04:31,800 --> 02:04:32,800
How are you?

1377
02:04:34,160 --> 02:04:35,160
I'm fine.

1378
02:04:39,840 --> 02:04:40,960
I know you're not fine.

1379
02:04:45,160 --> 02:04:47,600
What happened at the
shore wasn't normal either.

1380
02:04:53,080 --> 02:04:55,560
As if everything about
us is so normal, right?

1381
02:04:56,480 --> 02:04:58,720
Like what happened at the shore was normal.

1382
02:04:59,520 --> 02:05:02,240
We haven't had a normal
experience for a long time, Ateş.

1383
02:05:03,600 --> 02:05:04,600
Especially me.

1384
02:05:10,120 --> 02:05:11,960
You all drove me crazy together.

1385
02:05:16,000 --> 02:05:17,000
Forgive me.

1386
02:05:24,200 --> 02:05:26,760
Mother Müzeyyen can
be very cruel sometimes.

1387
02:05:29,360 --> 02:05:30,360
Sometimes?

1388
02:05:31,440 --> 02:05:33,400
You've forgotten what
was done to me, I guess?

1389
02:05:34,800 --> 02:05:35,800
I haven't forgotten.

1390
02:05:41,800 --> 02:05:42,800
And I won't...

1391
02:05:46,040 --> 02:05:49,120
But you see why we
can't be together, right?

1392
02:05:53,640 --> 02:05:55,880
The past won't let go of any of us.

1393
02:06:03,160 --> 02:06:06,440
If Nezir came now, would you still
be able to say those things to me?

1394
02:06:09,800 --> 02:06:11,400
Don't kid yourself, Ateş.

1395
02:06:13,080 --> 02:06:14,600
When you were jealous of Nezir...

1396
02:06:15,640 --> 02:06:17,880
When you stopped Mrs. Müzeyyen just now...

1397
02:06:18,520 --> 02:06:21,840
When you picked up the pieces in
the kitchen so I wouldn't get hurt…

1398
02:06:22,800 --> 02:06:25,120
All of them bore the traces
of the love you have for me.

1399
02:06:31,320 --> 02:06:33,880
I'm not so stupid that I
wouldn't understand that.

1400
02:06:49,720 --> 02:06:51,040
You love me.

1401
02:07:13,120 --> 02:07:14,240
And I love you too.

1402
02:07:20,320 --> 02:07:21,960
No one...

1403
02:07:22,800 --> 02:07:25,200
no one can tear you out of my heart.

1404
02:07:27,640 --> 02:07:29,240
Neither the anger you feel for my father

1405
02:07:29,960 --> 02:07:31,760
nor Mrs. Müzeyyen's
hatred can achieve that.

1406
02:07:37,400 --> 02:07:40,120
I understand what you've lived through.

1407
02:07:41,840 --> 02:07:43,720
I'm aware of the pain you've suffered.

1408
02:07:52,000 --> 02:07:53,560
Your lost childhood...

1409
02:07:55,520 --> 02:07:57,240
The sister you lost…

1410
02:08:03,280 --> 02:08:06,520
When I think about these, I
find your anger so justified…

1411
02:08:07,760 --> 02:08:11,080
All I want is to be by your side and...

1412
02:08:11,680 --> 02:08:12,840
to support you.

1413
02:08:13,240 --> 02:08:14,960
To heal your wounds.

1414
02:08:16,960 --> 02:08:18,440
But let go of the past now.

1415
02:08:20,560 --> 02:08:22,240
Look, we have a future.

1416
02:08:28,080 --> 02:08:29,080
-I— -Shh.

1417
02:08:36,160 --> 02:08:37,800
Please, don't say anything…

1418
02:08:45,480 --> 02:08:50,800
Sooner or later, my
childhood hero will return.

1419
02:08:57,240 --> 02:08:59,320
Until that day, I will wait patiently.

1420
02:09:07,240 --> 02:09:08,240
Look at me.

1421
02:09:09,720 --> 02:09:12,360
You are Tahir, don't forget that.

1422
02:10:46,640 --> 02:10:47,960
Hasn't Malik come yet?

1423
02:10:54,360 --> 02:10:55,360
-Malik? -Good evening.

1424
02:11:01,280 --> 02:11:02,720
Did you talk to Mr. Cemal?

1425
02:11:03,120 --> 02:11:04,200
I did.

1426
02:11:04,760 --> 02:11:07,800
He said I have to find the
passport. There's no other way.

1427
02:11:09,600 --> 02:11:13,960
Judging by your state, it's not
just about the passport. What happened?

1428
02:11:21,440 --> 02:11:24,040
Did something bad happen?
Did you get bad news?

1429
02:11:24,880 --> 02:11:26,600
Mr. Cemal told me...

1430
02:11:27,240 --> 02:11:28,800
He said someone reported me.

1431
02:11:29,280 --> 02:11:31,360
That's why all this is happening.

1432
02:11:32,160 --> 02:11:33,160
What?

1433
02:11:34,880 --> 02:11:35,880
What do you mean?

1434
02:11:36,440 --> 02:11:38,200
Reported me, that's what.

1435
02:11:38,520 --> 02:11:41,160
Someone specifically reported
me so I would be deported...

1436
02:11:46,000 --> 02:11:47,720
Who would be so hostile?

1437
02:11:50,120 --> 02:11:51,920
I have no idea, Aunt Binnaz.

1438
02:12:14,200 --> 02:12:15,440
I'll kill you!

1439
02:12:15,520 --> 02:12:17,040
What are you doing, let go of my arm!

1440
02:12:17,320 --> 02:12:19,520
You're always around Ateş!

1441
02:12:19,840 --> 02:12:20,960
Leave him alone!

1442
02:12:21,040 --> 02:12:22,640
Enough already! Get off his back!

1443
02:12:23,920 --> 02:12:25,120
I've told you before.

1444
02:12:25,880 --> 02:12:27,200
Don't get between Ateş and me!

1445
02:12:27,480 --> 02:12:29,560
What we go through is
none of your business!

1446
02:12:30,360 --> 02:12:34,280
And I've told you
repeatedly, there is no "us"!

1447
02:12:35,560 --> 02:12:37,000
Get this into your head.

1448
02:12:37,720 --> 02:12:39,200
Ateş and I won't break apart.

1449
02:12:40,320 --> 02:12:42,960
His storm will pass,
and he'll return to me.

1450
02:12:43,560 --> 02:12:45,200
You can never prevent that.

1451
02:12:45,800 --> 02:12:48,720
Because we love each
other. Do you understand?

1452
02:13:02,560 --> 02:13:04,960
I'll block it so well that…

1453
02:13:07,680 --> 02:13:09,800
you'll be out of our lives for good!

1454
02:13:10,200 --> 02:13:11,560
There's no other way!

1455
02:13:12,240 --> 02:13:13,760
What do you want from me?

1456
02:13:14,320 --> 02:13:16,800
Why do you care so much about Ateş and me?

1457
02:13:16,880 --> 02:13:18,560
I've made you my problem, yes.

1458
02:13:19,240 --> 02:13:20,680
Stay away from Ateş!

1459
02:13:22,000 --> 02:13:23,000
You are truly sick!

1460
02:13:23,440 --> 02:13:26,080
I don't want to deal
with you, get out of here!

1461
02:13:26,200 --> 02:13:27,200
I'm not leaving!

1462
02:13:27,800 --> 02:13:28,880
So that's how it is…

1463
02:13:33,280 --> 02:13:36,040
Then let me speak a
language you understand.

1464
02:13:46,920 --> 02:13:49,280
Ateş? I'm glad you're here.

1465
02:13:58,400 --> 02:14:01,160
We were just about to have
an inevitable conversation.

1466
02:14:01,640 --> 02:14:03,360
Get out, Aslı. Shut up.

1467
02:14:03,720 --> 02:14:04,720
I won't shut up.

1468
02:14:05,520 --> 02:14:07,360
Everyone is going to know everything now.

1469
02:14:08,000 --> 02:14:10,320
I'm tired of you wrapping
this girl in cotton wool!

1470
02:14:18,680 --> 02:14:23,080
She'll know the cost. And
at whose expense she lives…

1471
02:14:35,920 --> 02:14:38,920
It's not Haydar, you're the murderer!

1472
02:14:50,360 --> 02:14:52,480
She's the one who ruined your life!

1473
02:14:52,680 --> 02:14:53,680
Aslı, I said stop!

1474
02:14:57,280 --> 02:14:58,280
What do you mean?

1475
02:15:01,920 --> 02:15:03,520
You are Eylül's murderer!

1476
02:15:16,720 --> 02:15:18,440
They killed her because of you.

1477
02:15:30,000 --> 02:15:32,280
-Aslı, enough! -It's not enough!

1478
02:15:34,240 --> 02:15:37,480
The kidney you're
carrying is Eylül's kidney.

1479
02:15:40,120 --> 02:15:43,360
The kidney you're
carrying is Eylül's kidney.

1480
02:15:51,800 --> 02:15:54,840
They killed her so you could live!
